module.exports = /*#__PURE__*/JSON.parse('[{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Quick Insights from Spreadsheets","prompt":"\\"I have a spreadsheet with [describe: e.g., monthly sales for 12 months].\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify the top 3 trends\\n2. Create 3 simple charts for my manager\\n3. Explain any unusual patterns in plain language\\n4. Suggest 2 questions I should investigate further\\n\\nData: [paste or describe]\\"","tags":["finance","excel","quick-analysis","non-technical","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time analysts, small datasets, quick summaries","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A plain-English readout of the top three trends, three chart specs you can paste into Excel, and two follow-up questions for the business.","inputs":[{"label":"describe: e.g., monthly sales for 12 months"},{"label":"paste or describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Top 3 trends**\\n1. Revenue grew 14% YoY, accelerating in Q3 (+22% vs. +9% Q1)\\n2. EMEA outpaced APAC for the first time in 18 months\\n3. Promo months (Mar, Sep) drove 31% of annual revenue\\n\\n**Charts to build**\\n- Line: monthly revenue vs. prior year (12 + 12 points)\\n- Stacked bar: revenue by region per quarter\\n- Scatter: promo spend vs. incremental revenue\\n\\n**Unusual pattern:** August dip of −7% breaks the seasonal pattern. Worth asking ops.\\n\\n**Investigate**\\n- Is the August dip a stocking issue or genuine demand?\\n- Does the EMEA acceleration hold without the FX tailwind?"},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Rolling Forecast Model","prompt":"\\"I need to build a rolling forecast model for [product line/region].\\n\\nCurrent situation:\\n- Historical data: [describe]\\n- Planning horizon: [e.g., 12 months]\\n- Key drivers: [seasonality, promotions, market trends]\\n- Constraints: [budget, headcount, etc.]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Design the forecast structure\\n2. Suggest the best Excel/Google Sheets layout\\n3. Create formulas for key calculations\\n4. Identify risks and sensitivities\\n5. Build a variance analysis template\\n\\nOutput as a step-by-step implementation guide.\\"","tags":["forecasting","excel","financial-modeling","planning","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts, business controllers, budget managers","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A structured 5-step build plan: model layout, formula spec, risk table, and a variance-analysis template — all wired to your historicals.","inputs":[{"label":"product line/region"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"e.g., 12 months"},{"label":"seasonality, promotions, market trends"},{"label":"budget, headcount, etc."}],"tools":["Claude","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Sheet structure**\\n- `Drivers` — assumptions table (one column per month, FY+1 rolling)\\n- `P&L` — revenue waterfall, cost of sales, opex, operating profit\\n- `Variance` — actuals vs. forecast, with auto-coloured deltas\\n- `Scenarios` — base / upside / downside via INDEX/CHOOSE\\n\\n**Key formulas**\\n```\\nRevenue = Units × Price × (1 + Seasonality_Idx)\\nGM%     = (Revenue − COGS) / Revenue\\nF\'cast  = IF(MONTH(TODAY()) ≥ B$3, Actual, Driver-based)\\n```\\n\\n**Risks & sensitivities**\\n1. Price elasticity unknown — model ±5%, ±10%\\n2. Promo cannibalisation — flag if uplift < 40%\\n3. FX exposure on EMEA revenue — hedge above $X"},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automated FP&A Pipeline","prompt":"\\"I\'m building an automated FP&A pipeline using Python. The system needs to:\\n\\n1. Ingest data from [ERP/source system]\\n2. Clean and validate financial data\\n3. Run predictive models for [forecast type]\\n4. Generate automated reports (PowerPoint/Excel)\\n5. Alert on anomalies\\n6. Maintain audit trail\\n\\nCurrent tech stack: [your tools]\\nData sources: [list]\\nPain points: [describe manual work]\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Python code skeleton with error handling\\n- Data validation rules\\n- Testing strategy\\n- Deployment approach\\n- Documentation template\\"","tags":["python","automation","data-pipeline","fp&a","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"Data engineers, senior analysts, technical finance leads","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A production-ready Python architecture: ingestion, validation, forecasting, alerting, and audit trail — with a deployment plan and testing strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"ERP/source system"},{"label":"forecast type"},{"label":"your tools"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"describe manual work"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nERP → Ingest (Airflow) → Validate (Great Expectations)\\n    → Transform (dbt) → Forecast (Prophet/SARIMA)\\n    → Report (python-pptx) → Alert (Slack/Email)\\n```\\n\\n**Code skeleton — validation step**\\n```python\\nfrom great_expectations.dataset import PandasDataset\\n\\ndef validate(df: pd.DataFrame) -> ValidationResult:\\n    ds = PandasDataset(df)\\n    ds.expect_column_values_to_not_be_null(\\"account_id\\")\\n    ds.expect_column_values_to_be_between(\\"amount\\", -1e9, 1e9)\\n    ds.expect_column_values_to_match_regex(\\"period\\", r\\"^\\\\d{4}-\\\\d{2}$\\")\\n    return ds.validate()\\n```\\n\\n**Testing:** 80%+ coverage on transforms; smoke-test full pipeline on synthetic 100-row sample daily."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"EXPERT","skill_emoji":"⚫","title":"Enterprise Financial Platform","prompt":"\\"Design an enterprise financial planning platform for a [industry] company with:\\n\\nScale:\\n- [X] business units\\n- [X] currencies\\n- [X] users (planners, approvers, viewers)\\n- [X] GB/TB of historical data\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Multi-scenario planning (base, upside, downside)\\n- Real-time consolidation\\n- Workflow approvals\\n- Version control\\n- Integration with [ERP/CRM/etc.]\\n- GDPR/SOX compliance\\n- Self-service reporting\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n- Architecture diagram (describe)\\n- Technology stack recommendation\\n- Data model\\n- Security framework\\n- Implementation phases (12-18 months)\\n- Team structure and hiring plan\\n- Total cost of ownership\\"","tags":["enterprise","architecture","financial-platform","strategy","multi-year","cto-level"],"best_for":"CFOs, VP Finance, Enterprise Architects","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"An 18-month transformation plan: architecture, stack, data model, security framework, hiring plan, and total cost of ownership.","inputs":[{"label":"industry"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"ERP/CRM/etc."}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-year","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Phases**\\n1. Months 0–3: Foundation — data warehouse (Snowflake), identity (Okta), governance.\\n2. Months 4–9: Core planning — Anaplan/Pigment migration, workflow approvals, multi-currency.\\n3. Months 10–14: Self-service — Power BI semantic layer, exec dashboards.\\n4. Months 15–18: AI overlay — forecast assistance, anomaly detection.\\n\\n**Stack:** Snowflake · dbt · Anaplan · Power BI · Okta · GitHub Actions\\n\\n**Org:** 1 Director, 3 Senior FP&A, 2 Data Eng, 1 Solutions Architect, 1 PM\\n\\n**TCO (3-yr):** $4.8–6.2 M (60% software, 30% people, 10% integrators)"},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Sales & Market Analysis","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Customer Feedback Summary","prompt":"\\"I need to analyze customer feedback from [surveys/reviews/calls].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Summarize main themes in simple language\\n2. Identify top 5 complaints\\n3. Suggest 3 quick wins\\n4. Create a simple tracking template\\n\\nFeedback samples: [paste 5-10 examples]\\"","tags":["sales","customer-insights","feedback-analysis","quick-win","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"Five clustered themes, the top five complaints with frequency, three quick wins, and a tracking template — drawn from your raw verbatims.","inputs":[{"label":"surveys/reviews/calls"},{"label":"paste 5-10 examples"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Themes** (n=87 verbatims)\\n- Onboarding friction (34%)\\n- Slow support response (22%)\\n- Missing integrations (18%)\\n- Pricing clarity (15%)\\n- Performance lag (11%)\\n\\n**Top complaints**\\n1. \\"Couldn\'t find where to start\\" — 28 mentions\\n2. \\"Waited 3+ days for a reply\\" — 19 mentions\\n3. \\"Doesn\'t connect to Slack\\" — 14 mentions\\n\\n**Quick wins**\\n- Add a guided first-run checklist (kills #1)\\n- Auto-acknowledge tickets within 5 min (softens #2)\\n- Build the Slack integration (clears #3)"},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Sales & Market Analysis","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Competitive Analysis","prompt":"\\"I need to analyze our competitive position in [market] for [product category].\\n\\nAvailable data:\\n- Our sales data: [describe]\\n- Competitor public info: [list]\\n- Market reports: [if any]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. SWOT analysis framework\\n2. Competitive pricing comparison\\n3. Market share estimation approach\\n4. 3 strategic scenarios with pros/cons\\n\\nOutput as a structured analysis for leadership.\\"","tags":["strategy","competitive-intelligence","market-analysis","presentation","half-day"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A SWOT, a pricing comparison, a market-share approach, and three strategic scenarios with pros/cons — packaged for the leadership memo.","inputs":[{"label":"market"},{"label":"product category"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"if any"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**SWOT (you vs. top 3)**\\n| | Strengths | Weaknesses |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| You | Product depth, NPS 62 | Slow GTM, no SMB pricing |\\n| Comp A | Brand, channel | Bloated UX |\\n| Comp B | Price, speed | Thin enterprise feature set |\\n\\n**Pricing band:** $49–$199/mo. You sit at $129 — premium-mid.\\n\\n**Scenarios**\\n1. Hold the line, fortify enterprise — defensible, slow growth.\\n2. Launch SMB tier @ $39 — opens TAM 3×, risks cannibalisation.\\n3. Acquire Comp B — instant channel, $80–120M, ~6 months to close."},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Sales & Market Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Real-Time Market Intelligence Dashboard","prompt":"\\"Build a real-time market intelligence dashboard using [Python/JS/PowerBI].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Track competitor pricing across [channels]\\n- Monitor review sentiment on [platforms]\\n- Alert on price changes (>5%)\\n- Generate weekly reports\\n- Integrate with [CRM/ERP]\\n\\nData sources: [web scraping/APIs/exports]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Technical architecture\\n- Data pipeline code\\n- Dashboard wireframes\\n- Maintenance procedures\\n- Cost estimates\\"","tags":["dashboard","real-time","competitive-intel","python","javascript","multi-week"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A full technical spec: scraping infra, data pipeline, alert thresholds, dashboard wireframe, and a cost estimate.","inputs":[{"label":"Python/JS/PowerBI"},{"label":"channels"},{"label":"platforms"},{"label":"CRM/ERP"},{"label":"web scraping/APIs/exports"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","JavaScript","Power BI","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nSources (Bright Data / RSS / APIs)\\n  → Queue (SQS) → Workers (Python, 5 replicas)\\n  → DB (Postgres) → API (FastAPI) → UI (Next.js + Tremor)\\n```\\n\\n**Alerts**\\n- Price change ≥5% within 24h → Slack #commercial\\n- New review with rating ≤2 → Slack #cx\\n- Competitor pricing page hash change → Email + Slack\\n\\n**Cost:** ~$420/mo (scraping $180, infra $140, monitoring $100). Maintenance: 4 hrs/week."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Operations & Supply Chain","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Process Improvement Ideas","prompt":"\\"I want to improve our [inventory/service/production] process.\\n\\nCurrent process: [describe briefly]\\nMain problems: [list 2-3]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Suggest 3 improvement ideas\\n2. Create a before/after comparison\\n3. Draft an email to propose this\\n4. List what data to track\\"","tags":["operations","process-improvement","lean","quick-win","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"Three concrete improvement ideas, a before/after side-by-side, a proposal email draft, and the metrics worth tracking.","inputs":[{"label":"inventory/service/production"},{"label":"describe briefly"},{"label":"list 2-3"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Three ideas**\\n1. **Batch the daily count** into one end-of-shift sweep (saves ~40 min/day).\\n2. **QR-tag the top-50 SKUs** so receiving scans instead of types.\\n3. **Auto-reorder** at min level via shared sheet (no more stockouts).\\n\\n**Before → After**\\n- Manual count, 5×/day → 1 scan, end-of-shift\\n- Receiving avg time: 12 min → 4 min\\n- Stockouts/month: 7 → ≤1\\n\\n**Email draft**\\n> Hi [manager], I\'ve mapped three changes to receiving that could save ~15 hrs/week without new tooling. Quick run-through Friday at 2pm?"},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Operations & Supply Chain","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Supply Chain Optimization","prompt":"\\"I need to optimize [supply chain/inventory/distribution] for [region/product].\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- [X] SKUs\\n- [X] warehouses\\n- Lead times: [describe]\\n- Inventory costs: [describe]\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- Budget: [range]\\n- Timeline: [deadline]\\n- Service level target: [X%]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Analyze inefficiencies\\n2. Propose 3 optimization scenarios\\n3. Calculate approximate ROI\\n4. Create implementation roadmap\\n5. Identify risks and mitigation\\"","tags":["supply-chain","operations-research","roi","optimization","half-day"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"An inefficiency map, three optimisation scenarios with ROI math, an implementation roadmap, and a risk register.","inputs":[{"label":"supply chain/inventory/distribution"},{"label":"region/product"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"range"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Inefficiencies found**\\n- 38% of SKUs sit in 2+ warehouses unnecessarily (carrying cost: $1.2M/yr)\\n- Lead time variance 4–18 days on a single supplier\\n- Safety stock set on rule-of-thumb, not service-level math\\n\\n**Scenarios**\\n| | Cost | Annual saving | Service level |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Consolidate to 3 DCs | $2.1M one-time | $1.8M | 97% |\\n| Add 4th regional DC | $3.4M one-time | $2.6M | 99% |\\n| Optimise w/o new DCs | $200k | $0.9M | 96% |\\n\\n**Risk:** scenario 1 risks weather concentration on the Memphis hub."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Customer Support","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Response Templates","prompt":"\\"I handle customer service. I often get questions about [topic].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Draft 5 standard responses\\n2. Create a troubleshooting flowchart for [issue]\\n3. Suggest information to collect\\n4. Write a team FAQ\\"","tags":["customer-service","templates","troubleshooting","training","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"Five reusable response templates, a troubleshooting flowchart for your common issue, an info-collection checklist, and a team FAQ.","inputs":[{"label":"topic"},{"label":"issue"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Templates**\\n1. **Acknowledgement** — \\"Got it, [name]. Looking into it now — back to you within 2 hours.\\"\\n2. **Asking for more info** — \\"Quick thing to unblock me: could you send [X, Y]?\\"\\n3. **Known issue** — \\"Yep, known one — fix is going out [date]. Workaround: [...]\\"\\n4. **Escalation** — \\"Pulling in [team]. Owner is [name]. Updates in this thread.\\"\\n5. **Resolution** — \\"[Fix] is live. Anything else from this ticket?\\"\\n\\n**Flowchart** (login issue): Reset password? → Y: send link / N: 2FA enrolled? → Y: code working? → escalate."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Customer Support","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"First Contact Resolution","prompt":"\\"I want to improve first-contact resolution in customer support.\\n\\nCurrent metrics:\\n- FCR rate: [X%]\\n- Avg handle time: [X min]\\n- CSAT: [X/10]\\n\\nCommon issues: [list categories]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Design a decision tree\\n2. Create response templates by type\\n3. Suggest training topics\\n4. Propose KPIs\\n5. Build quality monitoring checklist\\"","tags":["customer-service","quality","metrics","training","half-day"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"A decision tree, type-specific response templates, training topics, KPIs, and a quality monitoring checklist.","inputs":[{"label":"X%"},{"label":"X min"},{"label":"X/10"},{"label":"list categories"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Decision tree (login)**\\n```\\nIssue → Account locked?\\n├─ Y → Unlock + send reset → Resolved\\n└─ N → 2FA enrolled?\\n    ├─ Y → Codes working? → escalate L2 if no\\n    └─ N → Enrol + verify → Resolved\\n```\\n\\n**KPIs:** FCR (target 78%), AHT (≤6 min), CSAT (≥4.4/5), repeat-contact rate (≤8%).\\n\\n**QA checklist (per ticket)**\\n- [ ] Asked the diagnostic Q first\\n- [ ] Verified identity\\n- [ ] Logged root cause code\\n- [ ] Sent confirmation summary"},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Customer Support","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI Support Assistant","prompt":"\\"Build an AI-powered customer support assistant that can:\\n\\n1. Classify tickets by urgency and topic\\n2. Suggest solutions from knowledge base\\n3. Draft personalized responses\\n4. Escalate complex issues\\n5. Learn from corrections\\n\\nIntegration:\\n- Connect to [ticketing system]\\n- Access [knowledge base]\\n- Work in [language]\\n- GDPR compliant\\n\\nProvide:\\n- NLP pipeline architecture\\n- Training data requirements\\n- Model selection\\n- Implementation phases\\n- Success metrics\\"","tags":["ai-ml","nlp","customer-service","automation","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"An NLP pipeline architecture, training-data requirements, model selection, phased rollout, and success metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"ticketing system"},{"label":"knowledge base"},{"label":"language"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nTicket → Classifier (BERT, 12 classes)\\n       → KB retriever (embeddings + reranker)\\n       → Drafter (LLM, brand-tuned)\\n       → Human-in-loop (L1 review for low-confidence)\\n       → Send / Escalate\\n```\\n\\n**Training data:** ~5k labelled tickets minimum; 80/10/10 split; include 200 hard negatives.\\n\\n**Rollout:** shadow-mode (4 wk) → suggest-only (8 wk) → auto-send tier-1 (gated by confidence ≥0.92)."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI-Assisted Variance Analysis","prompt":"\\"I just closed the month and need to explain budget vs. actual variances to my manager.\\n\\nData:\\n- Budget: [amount or file]\\n- Actual: [amount or file]\\n- Key categories: [list]\\n- Previous month: [for comparison]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify the top 5 variances (positive and negative)\\n2. Write 2-3 sentence explanations for each\\n3. Flag which ones need action vs. which are noise\\n4. Draft the email/update for my manager\\n5. Suggest follow-up questions to ask the business\\"","tags":["fp&a","variance-analysis","month-end","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"First-time FP&A analysts, month-end close support","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance — \\"ChatGPT Just Replaced Hours of FP&A Work\\"","outcome":"The top five variances with one-paragraph explanations, an action vs. noise call on each, and a ready-to-send manager email.","inputs":[{"label":"amount or file"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"for comparison"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Top 5 variances (Oct vs. budget)**\\n| Account | Var | Driver |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Subscription rev | +$340k | Renewal pull-forward, treat as timing |\\n| Cloud infra | +$190k | Workload spike from new feature — investigate |\\n| T&E | −$60k | Conf budget unspent — flag for reforecast |\\n| Stock comp | +$110k | New hires — already accrued, noise |\\n| Hosting | +$45k | Egress overage — review architecture |\\n\\n**Action vs noise:** rows 2 and 5 need follow-up; the rest are timing/accrual noise.\\n\\n**Manager email:** drafted, ~120 words, ready to copy."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Automated Commentary Writing","prompt":"\\"I need to write monthly financial commentary for [report/steerco].\\n\\nData available:\\n- P&L summary\\n- Key metrics (revenue, margin, opex)\\n- Variance to budget and prior year\\n- Business highlights\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Draft executive summary (3-4 bullets)\\n2. Write narrative for each section\\n3. Use professional but concise language\\n4. Highlight red flags\\n5. Suggest graphics/tables to include\\"","tags":["fp&a","commentary","reporting","writing","1-hour"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts spending hours writing commentary","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance","outcome":"An executive-summary block, narrative sections for each P&L line, professional phrasing, red-flag highlights, and graphic suggestions.","inputs":[{"label":"report/steerco"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Executive summary**\\n- Revenue $42.1M, +6.2% YoY, in line with budget\\n- GM% 68.1%, +120bps vs. prior year — pricing actions holding\\n- Opex tracking $0.4M favourable; hiring lag in R&D\\n- Operating income $12.6M; FX headwind of −$0.3M absorbed\\n\\n**Revenue narrative**\\n> Subscription revenue grew 9% YoY, offsetting a 4% decline in services. New-logo ARR up 14%, but expansion softened to 11% (vs. 16% prior quarter), consistent with the broader macro slowdown observed by peers.\\n\\n**Red flag:** R&D under-hire risks Q1 product timeline."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI-Powered Forecasting Assistant","prompt":"\\"I need to build/update a forecast with AI assistance.\\n\\nHistorical data:\\n- [X] months of actuals\\n- Seasonality patterns\\n- Known one-off events\\n\\nCurrent forecast:\\n- Budget: [amount]\\n- Current projection: [amount]\\n- Risk factors: [list]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Analyze historical trends\\n2. Identify seasonality and patterns\\n3. Adjust for known events\\n4. Generate 3 scenarios (base/upside/downside)\\n5. Write the forecast narrative\\n6. Create summary for leadership\\n\\nOutput in structured format with formulas if applicable.\\"","tags":["fp&a","forecasting","scenario-planning","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"Business controllers, FP&A managers doing rolling forecasts","source":"Inside FP&A — \\"How AI is Changing FP&A\\"","outcome":"A trend + seasonality breakdown, adjustments for known events, three scenarios, and the narrative for leadership.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"amount"},{"label":"list"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Trend & seasonality**\\n- 18-month CAGR: +12% (2.4% MoM)\\n- Seasonality peak: Nov–Dec (+38% vs. trailing 3 mo)\\n- Soft month: Feb (−18%)\\n\\n**Scenarios (FY+1)**\\n| | Revenue | GM% | OI |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Base | $186M | 67% | $42M |\\n| Upside (Enterprise +20%) | $204M | 69% | $52M |\\n| Downside (Churn 2pp) | $171M | 65% | $35M |\\n\\n**Narrative:** \\"Base assumes 11% growth, in line with H2 run rate. Upside flips on enterprise pipeline conversion above 32% — feasible if security review accelerates.\\"*"},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Financial Modeling with AI","prompt":"\\"I\'m building a financial model for [purpose: M&A/new product/investment].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- 3-statement model (P&L, BS, CF)\\n- 5-year projection\\n- Sensitivity analysis\\n- Key assumptions clearly documented\\n\\nCurrent stage: [blank template / partial model / needs review]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Structure the model layout\\n2. Build core formulas and drivers\\n3. Create assumption tables\\n4. Add sensitivity tables (±10%, ±20%)\\n5. Build summary dashboard\\n6. Add error checks and validations\\n7. Write documentation\\n\\nFormat: [Excel/Google Sheets]\\n\\nInclude:\\n- Color coding scheme\\n- Formula explanations\\n- Circularity handling\\n- Audit trail\\"","tags":["fp&a","financial-modeling","excel","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A managers, corporate development, investment analysts","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance","outcome":"A complete 3-statement model spec: structure, drivers, sensitivities, dashboard, audit checks, and documentation.","inputs":[{"label":"purpose: M&A/new product/investment"},{"label":"blank template / partial model / needs review"},{"label":"Excel/Google Sheets"}],"tools":["Claude","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Tabs**\\n1. `Cover` — purpose, version, owner\\n2. `Drivers` — colour-coded inputs (blue)\\n3. `P&L`, `BS`, `CF` — links only (black), no hardcodes\\n4. `Sensitivity` — ±10/20% on revenue growth × GM\\n5. `Checks` — 6 integrity rules (BS balances, CF reconciles)\\n\\n**Driver math (revenue)**\\n```\\nRev_t = Cust_t × ARPU_t\\nCust_t = Cust_{t-1} × (1 − Churn_t) + NewLogo_t\\n```\\n\\n**Checks:** all return PASS or the cell turns red. Circularity resolved with iterative calc, max 100, threshold 0.001."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Board Presentation Builder","prompt":"\\"I need to create a board/executive presentation on [financial topic].\\n\\nAudience: [Board/CFO/CEO]\\nTime: [X minutes]\\nKey message: [one sentence]\\nData available: [describe]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Story arc (beginning, middle, end)\\n2. Slide-by-slide outline\\n3. Key charts/visuals to include\\n4. Speaker notes with timing\\n5. Appendix with backup data\\n6. Q&A preparation (anticipate 5 questions)\\n\\nMake it:\\n- Executive-level (not operational)\\n- Visual and scannable\\n- Persuasive, not just informative\\n- Action-oriented\\"","tags":["fp&a","presentation","board","executive","storytelling","half-day"],"best_for":"Directors and VPs presenting to C-suite","source":"Inside FP&A","outcome":"A story arc, slide-by-slide outline, chart picks, timed speaker notes, a backup appendix, and five anticipated questions with answers.","inputs":[{"label":"financial topic"},{"label":"Board/CFO/CEO"},{"label":"X minutes"},{"label":"one sentence"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Story arc**\\n1. Where we are (one slide, one number)\\n2. What changed since last board (3 deltas)\\n3. What\'s working / what isn\'t\\n4. The decision we\'re asking for\\n5. What happens if you say yes\\n\\n**Slides** (15 min total)\\n1. Title + headline number (45s)\\n2. Q3 scorecard vs. plan (90s)\\n3. The two wins (2 min)\\n4. The two concerns (2 min)\\n5. Pricing decision — recommendation (3 min)\\n6. Asks + timeline (1 min)\\n\\n**Anticipated Q1:** \\"What\'s the downside case?\\" — answer prepped, 2 sentences + 1 backup slide."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"FP&A Process Automation","prompt":"\\"I want to automate [specific FP&A process] that currently takes [X hours/week].\\n\\nCurrent process:\\n1. [Manual step 1]\\n2. [Manual step 2]\\n3. [Manual step 3]\\n\\nInputs: [data sources]\\nOutputs: [deliverables]\\nFrequency: [monthly/weekly/ad-hoc]\\n\\nPlease design:\\n1. Process map (as-is vs. to-be)\\n2. Automation approach\\n3. Tool selection (Excel macros/Python/Power Automate)\\n4. Error handling\\n5. Validation checks\\n6. Documentation\\n7. Change management plan\\n\\nFocus on:\\n- Audit trail\\n- Data integrity\\n- Scalability\\n- Maintainability\\"","tags":["fp&a","automation","process-improvement","advanced","multi-week"],"best_for":"Senior FP&A managers, finance transformation leads","source":"Mike\'s F9 Finance + Inside FP&A","outcome":"A process map (as-is vs. to-be), automation approach, tool selection, error handling, validation, and a change-management plan.","inputs":[{"label":"specific FP&A process"},{"label":"X hours/week"},{"label":"Manual step 1"},{"label":"Manual step 2"},{"label":"Manual step 3"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**As-is (12 hrs/wk)**\\n1. Pull exports from SAP, Salesforce, ADP (3 hrs)\\n2. Stitch in Excel (5 hrs)\\n3. Manual variance commentary (3 hrs)\\n4. Format deck (1 hr)\\n\\n**To-be (~1 hr/wk)**\\n1. Python pulls from APIs nightly\\n2. dbt transforms + tests\\n3. LLM drafts commentary from variance table\\n4. python-pptx generates deck\\n\\n**Tool stack:** Python · dbt · Anthropic API · python-pptx · Airflow\\n\\n**Change mgmt:** 4-week parallel run, weekly QA, sign-off from controller before cutover."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI-Powered Financial Analysis Pipeline","prompt":"\\"Build an AI-assisted financial analysis system for [company/department].\\n\\nScope:\\n- Monthly variance analysis (automated commentary)\\n- Rolling forecast updates\\n- Scenario modeling\\n- Executive summary generation\\n- Ad-hoc analysis support\\n\\nData sources:\\n- ERP: [system]\\n- BI tool: [system]\\n- Excel files: [describe]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Automated commentary generation\\n- Natural language queries (\\"What drove revenue variance?\\")\\n- Anomaly detection\\n- Trend identification\\n- Predictive alerts\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Data pipeline design\\n- AI model selection and training approach\\n- Integration plan\\n- Governance framework\\n- ROI calculation\\"","tags":["fp&a","ai-pipeline","automation","nlp","advanced","multi-month"],"best_for":"Finance transformation teams, data-driven FP&A organizations","source":"Inside FP&A — \\"How AI is Changing FP&A\\"","outcome":"A complete AI-assisted FP&A system: architecture, data pipeline, model selection, integration plan, governance, and ROI math.","inputs":[{"label":"company/department"},{"label":"system"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Multi-month","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nERP/BI → Data lake (Snowflake)\\n       → Feature store (Feast)\\n       → LLM layer (Claude / GPT-4) ← embeddings of GL + commentary corpus\\n       → NL query interface (LangChain agent)\\n       → Outputs: commentary, anomaly alerts, forecast deltas\\n```\\n\\n**Governance:** every AI-generated number gets a citation back to the source row; commentary stored with prompt + version hash for audit.\\n\\n**ROI:** ~$240k/yr saved (1.5 FTE equivalent) against $80k build + $35k/yr run cost. Payback < 6 months."},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"FP&A & Financial Analysis (AI-Powered)","skill_level":"EXPERT","skill_emoji":"⚫","title":"Enterprise FP&A Transformation","prompt":"\\"Design an AI-enabled FP&A transformation for a [industry] company.\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- [X] FTEs in FP&A\\n- Manual processes: [list]\\n- Tools: [Excel/SAP/Oracle/etc.]\\n- Cycle times: [describe]\\n\\nTarget state (3-5 years):\\n- Automated forecasting\\n- Self-service analytics\\n- Real-time dashboards\\n- AI-powered insights\\n- Zero-based reporting\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Transformation roadmap (phases)\\n2. Technology stack\\n3. Organization design\\n4. Skill development plan\\n5. Change management approach\\n6. Investment case (cost/benefit)\\n7. Risk assessment\\n8. Success metrics\\n9. Vendor evaluation criteria\\"","tags":["fp&a","transformation","strategy","enterprise","expert","multi-year"],"best_for":"CFOs, VP Finance, Finance Directors leading transformation","source":"Inside FP&A","outcome":"A phased 3–5 year roadmap with org design, tech stack, investment case, risks, vendor criteria, and success metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"industry"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"Excel/SAP/Oracle/etc."},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Multi-year","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Phases**\\n- Yr 1 — Foundations: cloud DW, identity, governance, dashboarding standard\\n- Yr 2 — Planning: replace spreadsheet plan with Anaplan/Pigment\\n- Yr 3 — AI overlay: automated commentary, anomaly detection, NL queries\\n\\n**Org shift**\\n- FP&A FTEs: 24 → 18 (reskill 6 into analytics engineers)\\n- New roles: 2 ML engineers, 1 finance data steward\\n\\n**Investment case (3-yr)**\\n- Spend: $9.6M\\n- Savings: $14.2M (productivity, cycle-time reduction)\\n- Net: +$4.6M, payback yr 2.5\\n\\n**Risks:** vendor lock-in (mitigate with semantic layer), change fatigue (sequence releases)."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI-Powered Spreadsheet Analysis","prompt":"\\"I have a spreadsheet with [describe data]. I need to analyze it using AI.\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify trends and patterns\\n2. Highlight anomalies or outliers\\n3. Create summary statistics\\n4. Generate 3 key insights\\n5. Suggest visualizations\\n\\nData context: [industry/business context]\\nFormat: [Excel/Google Sheets]\\n\\nOutput as a structured analysis I can share.\\"","tags":["excel","google-sheets","data-analysis","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"Analysts new to AI-assisted spreadsheet work","source":"OpenAI — \\"ChatGPT for Excel and Google Sheets\\"","outcome":"A structured analysis with trends, anomalies, summary stats, three insights, and chart recommendations — shareable as-is.","inputs":[{"label":"describe data"},{"label":"industry/business context"},{"label":"Excel/Google Sheets"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Trends**\\n- Northeast region revenue +18% YoY, leading other regions by 9pp\\n- Q4 still concentrates 38% of annual sales (vs. 34% three years ago)\\n\\n**Anomalies**\\n- Two SKUs (#A23, #A41) show unit volume +200% but revenue flat — pricing issue?\\n- Negative gross margin on three loss-leaders in Mar\\n\\n**Summary stats:** mean order $187, median $124, p90 $412. Long tail dominated by enterprise.\\n\\n**Suggested visuals:** waterfall of YoY revenue by region; scatter of unit volume vs. price for the SKU set."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Natural Language Excel Updates","prompt":"\\"Update the worksheet tab called @[TAB NAME] with the latest [data type] using [data source].\\n\\nExample: \'Update the worksheet tab called @Balance Sheet - Q with the latest earnings print and transcript commentary using S&P Global\'\\n\\nContext:\\n- Workbook: [name]\\n- Tab: [specific tab]\\n- Data source: [S&P Global/Bloomberg/internal]\\n- Time period: [Q1/Q2/etc.]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Pull latest actuals and replace estimates\\n2. Update column headers (E → A for actual)\\n3. Add variance commentary\\n4. Verify checks = PASS\\n5. Log data sources\\"","tags":["excel","financial-modeling","automation","beginner","fp&a"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts doing quarterly updates","source":"OpenAI — \\"ChatGPT for Excel and Google Sheets\\"","outcome":"Latest actuals pulled into the tab you named, column headers swapped from E → A, variance commentary inline, and a source log appended.","inputs":[{"label":"TAB NAME"},{"label":"data type"},{"label":"data source"},{"label":"name"},{"label":"specific tab"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel"],"est_time":"5–10 min","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Updates to @Balance Sheet - Q3**\\n- Q3 actuals replaced estimates in columns C:F (source: S&P Capital IQ, pulled 2026-05-12 09:14 UTC)\\n- Headers: \\"Q3 E\\" → \\"Q3 A\\"\\n- New row: variance commentary\\n- All checks PASS ✓\\n\\n**Variance commentary inserted**\\n> Cash +$28M vs. estimate, driven by working-capital improvement (DSO ↓ 4 days). Long-term debt unchanged. Goodwill recalibrated for the X acquisition.\\n\\n**Source log:** appended to `_meta` tab; includes URL, retrieval time, fields touched."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"AI-Assisted Financial Model Audit","prompt":"\\"Audit my financial model for consistency and errors.\\n\\nModel details:\\n- Purpose: [DCF/3-statement/budget]\\n- Time horizon: [years]\\n- Key assumptions: [list]\\n- Check cells: [locations]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Verify assumption consistency and sign\\n2. Check formula links and circularities\\n3. Validate check cells = 0 or PASS\\n4. Identify broken links or #REF errors\\n5. Flag unusual patterns (e.g., margins jumping 50%)\\n6. Suggest improvements\\n\\nOutput: Audit report with severity ratings (Critical/Warning/Info)\\"","tags":["excel","financial-modeling","audit","intermediate","fp&a","half-day"],"best_for":"Senior analysts reviewing models before board submission","source":"OpenAI — \\"ChatGPT for Excel and Google Sheets\\"","outcome":"An audit report with severity-tagged findings: assumption consistency, formula integrity, broken links, anomalies, and improvements.","inputs":[{"label":"DCF/3-statement/budget"},{"label":"years"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"locations"}],"tools":["Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Critical (3)**\\n- `WACC!C18` references a deleted range — #REF!\\n- BS doesn\'t balance in years 4–5: $1.2M, $0.9M off\\n- Tax rate hard-coded inside a formula in CF tab\\n\\n**Warnings (7)**\\n- Revenue growth jumps 14% → 41% Y3 with no driver explanation\\n- Two circularities resolved silently — flag for review\\n- Three named ranges declared but unused\\n\\n**Info (12)** — naming, colour coding, font drift.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** fix criticals before sending; warnings before signing."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Power BI Model Optimization with AI","prompt":"\\"Analyze my Power BI model and optimize it.\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- Tables: [X]\\n- Measures: [X]\\n- Size: [X MB]\\n- Refresh time: [X minutes]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Analyze naming conventions and suggest renames\\n2. Add display folders to organize fields\\n3. Hide foreign key columns (show only friendly names)\\n4. Add descriptions to all measures and columns\\n5. Create user hierarchies for drill-down\\n6. Optimize data types for compression\\n7. Generate complete documentation\\n\\nOutput: Step-by-step implementation guide with DAX code\\"","tags":["powerbi","dax","data-modeling","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"BI developers, data modelers","source":"Power BI Bro — \\"Claude + Power BI Integration via MCP\\"","outcome":"A naming + organisation rewrite, hidden FK columns, descriptions on every measure, drill hierarchies, type-optimised columns, and full documentation.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"X MB"},{"label":"X minutes"}],"tools":["Claude","Power BI"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Suggested renames**\\n- `fact_sale_qty_v2` → `Sales Quantity`\\n- `dim_cust_full` → `Customer`\\n- `_calc_yoy_pct` → `Revenue YoY %`\\n\\n**Display folders added**\\n- `Sales\\\\Volume` — Units, Returns, Net Units\\n- `Sales\\\\Value` — Revenue, GM, GM%\\n- `Time Intel` — YoY, MTD, QTD measures\\n\\n**Optimisation**\\n- 14 string cols converted to integer keys → file size 89 MB → 41 MB\\n- Refresh time: 14 min → 6 min\\n\\n**Doc output:** 28-page Markdown + Mermaid relationship diagram."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Create Calculation Table with Measures","prompt":"\\"Create a new empty table to hold calculations, create an aggregate amount calc for every [category] value, create a net calc, and also create a comprehensive group of monthly time intelligence measures for all measures created. Remove/hide any placeholder fields in the new table.\\"","tags":["powerbi","dax","measures","intermediate","quick-win"],"best_for":"BI developers building semantic models","source":"Power BI Bro — \\"Claude + Power BI Integration via MCP\\"","outcome":"A new measure table, an aggregate-amount calc per category value, a Net measure, and a full suite of monthly time-intelligence measures — placeholder fields hidden.","inputs":[{"label":"category"}],"tools":["Claude","Power BI"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**New table:** `_Measures`\\n\\n**Per category:**\\n```dax\\n[Sales — Hardware] = CALCULATE([Sales Amount], \'Product\'[Category] = \\"Hardware\\")\\n[Sales — Software] = CALCULATE([Sales Amount], \'Product\'[Category] = \\"Software\\")\\n[Sales — Services] = CALCULATE([Sales Amount], \'Product\'[Category] = \\"Services\\")\\n```\\n\\n**Net:** `Net Sales = [Sales Amount] − [Returns Amount]`\\n\\n**Time intel (for each measure):** MTD, QTD, YTD, MoM, YoY, Rolling 3M, Rolling 12M.\\n\\nPlaceholder integer column `_placeholder` hidden from report view."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Cube Function Dashboard (Excel)","prompt":"\\"I want to build a custom dashboard using Excel Cube functions instead of PivotTables.\\n\\nData model: [Power Pivot / SSAS / Power BI]\\nMetrics needed: [list]\\nLayout requirements: [custom spacing, narration, totals]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Create CUBESET for each dimension (months, products, regions)\\n2. Use CUBEMEMBER for row/column labels\\n3. Use CUBEVALUE to pull calculated measures\\n4. Add CUBERANKEDMEMBER for Top N rankings\\n5. Apply conditional formatting with CUBEKPIMEMBER\\n6. Build flexible layout (not PivotTable rigid)\\n\\nProvide: Complete formulas and layout guide\\"","tags":["excel","cube-functions","cubedata","dashboard","intermediate","half-day"],"best_for":"FP&A analysts building custom financial dashboards","source":"Finex Skills Hub — \\"Master 6 Excel Cube Functions\\"","outcome":"A custom Excel cube-function dashboard: CUBESET dimensions, CUBEMEMBER labels, CUBEVALUE measures, Top-N ranks, and KPI conditional formatting.","inputs":[{"label":"Power Pivot / SSAS / Power BI"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"custom spacing, narration, totals"}],"tools":["Claude","Excel","Power BI"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Cell formulas (sample)**\\n```\\nA4:  =CUBEMEMBER(\\"Model\\",\\"[Date].[Calendar].[Month].&[2026-04]\\")\\nB4:  =CUBEVALUE(\\"Model\\",\\"[Measures].[Revenue]\\", A4, $A$1)\\nC4:  =CUBEVALUE(\\"Model\\",\\"[Measures].[Revenue YoY %]\\", A4, $A$1)\\nA20: =CUBERANKEDMEMBER(\\"Model\\",\\"[Product].[Top 10]\\",1)\\n```\\n\\n**Layout:** quarter-bands in rows, scenarios in columns, two narration columns between sections — impossible to do this cleanly with a PivotTable."},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI-Powered BI Documentation Generator","prompt":"\\"Generate a Markdown document (.md) that provides complete, professional documentation for the [Power BI Semantic Model / Excel Data Model], including a data dictionary.\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Use a simple mermaid diagram to illustrate table relationships\\n- Document each measure including the DAX code and description of business logic\\n- Use business-friendly names\\n- Document data sources by analyzing the Power Query code\\n- Include executive summary, table of contents, model diagrams\\n- Add usage guidelines and reporting scenarios\\n\\nCurrent model: [describe or attach .pbix]\\n\\nOutput: Enterprise-grade documentation (~60 pages)\\"","tags":["powerbi","documentation","data-dictionary","advanced","multi-day"],"best_for":"BI teams, Center of Excellence leads","source":"Power BI Bro — \\"Claude + Power BI Integration via MCP\\"","outcome":"A complete ~60-page Markdown doc with executive summary, mermaid relationship diagram, per-measure DAX + plain-English business logic, data sources, and usage scenarios.","inputs":[{"label":"Power BI Semantic Model / Excel Data Model"},{"label":"describe or attach .pbix"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel","Power BI"],"est_time":"2–4 days","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Generated Markdown (excerpt)**\\n```markdown\\n## Model overview\\nThis semantic model serves the Commercial Reporting team and powers\\n12 reports, 3 Power BI Apps, and 1 paginated weekly board pack.\\n\\n## Relationship diagram\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`mermaid\\nflowchart LR\\n  Date --> Sales\\n  Customer --> Sales\\n  Product --> Sales\\n  Sales --> InvoiceLine\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n\\n## Measures\\n### Revenue\\n**DAX**\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`dax\\nRevenue = SUMX(\'Sales\', \'Sales\'[Quantity] * \'Sales\'[Unit Price])\\n\\\\`\\\\`\\\\`\\n**Business logic:** sales revenue net of returns, recognised on shipment.\\n```"},{"domain":"Data & Analytics","section":"Data Analytics & Business Intelligence (BI)","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Autonomous Workflow System","prompt":"\\"I want to build [X] proactive AI workflows that run automatically.\\n\\nCurrent manual tasks:\\n1. [Task 1 — frequency]\\n2. [Task 2 — frequency]\\n3. [Task 3 — frequency]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Schedule-based execution (daily/weekly)\\n- Email/rss/notification delivery\\n- Self-directed (no manual kickoff)\\n- Multi-agent coordination\\n\\nExample workflows to replicate:\\n1. Morning briefing (industry news, competitor updates)\\n2. Friday email recap (unresponded urgent emails ranked by urgency)\\n3. Weekly financial summary (variance analysis auto-generated)\\n4. Monday forecast update (rolling forecast refresh)\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Architecture for 36+ workflows\\n- Agent hierarchy design (master agents + sub-agents)\\n- Scheduling framework\\n- Integration approach (Claude Co-work / Codex / Cloud Code)\\n- Monitoring and error handling\\"","tags":["automation","workflows","agents","advanced","productivity","multi-week"],"best_for":"AI power users, productivity hackers, executives","source":"Alli Miller (ex-Amazon AI leader) — \\"Ex-Amazon AI Leader Interview\\"","outcome":"A blueprint for 36+ scheduled AI workflows: agent hierarchy, scheduling, integration with Claude Code / Codex / Cloud Code, monitoring, and error handling.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"Task 1 — frequency"},{"label":"Task 2 — frequency"},{"label":"Task 3 — frequency"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Hierarchy**\\n```\\nMaster agent (daily 06:00 UTC)\\n├─ Morning briefing sub-agent → industry news + competitor moves\\n├─ Calendar sub-agent → today\'s meetings + prep\\n└─ Unblocked-tasks sub-agent → cross-checks email + Slack\\n\\nFriday 16:00 UTC\\n└─ Email recap sub-agent → urgent unresponded, ranked\\n```\\n\\n**Stack:** Claude Code + cron + S3 (state) + Slack/email (delivery).\\n\\n**Monitoring:** every run writes structured log; dashboard alerts on >2 consecutive failures or runtime drift >2σ."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Task & Time Management","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Overwhelm Recovery","prompt":"\\"I feel overwhelmed. I am [role] and struggle with [specific problem].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Prioritize tasks using a simple framework\\n2. Create a daily/weekly schedule template\\n3. Suggest 3 focus habits\\n4. Recommend tools for [Mac/Windows/Phone]\\"","tags":["productivity","time-management","beginner-friendly","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A prioritisation framework, a daily + weekly schedule template, three focus habits, and platform-specific tool picks.","inputs":[{"label":"role"},{"label":"specific problem"},{"label":"Mac/Windows/Phone"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Prioritisation (Eisenhower + energy)**\\n1. Urgent + important + high-energy first hour\\n2. Important not urgent → schedule into deep-work blocks\\n3. Urgent not important → batch into a 30-min slot\\n4. Neither → delete, don\'t defer\\n\\n**Daily template**\\n- 09:00–10:30 — Deep work block 1 (Slack off, phone away)\\n- 10:30–11:00 — Email / Slack triage\\n- 11:00–12:30 — Deep work block 2\\n- Afternoon: meetings + lighter work\\n\\n**Habits:** (1) inbox-zero by 17:00, (2) one weekly review, (3) 50-min focus, 10-min reset.\\n\\n**Mac tools:** Things 3, Cron, Raycast."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Task & Time Management","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Personal Productivity System","prompt":"\\"I want to build a personal productivity system.\\n\\nCurrent tools: [Notion/Obsidian/Todoist/etc.]\\nWork style: [remote/hybrid/office]\\nMain challenges: [context switching/meetings/deep work]\\n\\nPlease design:\\n1. PARA-style organization\\n2. Weekly review process\\n3. Meeting notes template\\n4. Project tracking dashboard\\n5. Automation workflows\\n\\nOutput as a setup guide.\\"","tags":["productivity","notion","obsidian","system-design","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A PARA-style organisation scheme, a weekly review process, meeting and project templates, and lightweight automations.","inputs":[{"label":"Notion/Obsidian/Todoist/etc."},{"label":"remote/hybrid/office"},{"label":"context switching/meetings/deep work"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Obsidian"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**PARA**\\n- `01-Projects` — active, with a deadline (≤6)\\n- `02-Areas` — ongoing responsibilities (Health, Finance, Team)\\n- `03-Resources` — references you\'ll consult\\n- `04-Archive` — done or paused\\n\\n**Weekly review (Fri 16:00, 45 min)**\\n1. Clear inbox, calendar, and capture tray\\n2. Move stale projects to Archive\\n3. Pick three priorities for next week\\n4. Two-line journal entry\\n\\n**Automation:** Calendar → Notion meeting note auto-created with attendees + agenda block."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Task & Time Management","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automated Productivity System","prompt":"\\"Build an automated personal productivity system that:\\n\\n1. Collects tasks from [email/Slack/calendar]\\n2. Prioritizes with Eisenhower + AI scoring\\n3. Schedules deep work blocks\\n4. Tracks time automatically\\n5. Generates weekly reports\\n6. Integrates with [calendar/task manager]\\n\\nCurrent stack: [your tools]\\nTechnical skills: [your level]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Automation scripts\\n- Data flow diagram\\n- Customization options\\"","tags":["automation","python","javascript","api-integration","multi-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An end-to-end personal productivity automation: task ingestion, AI scoring, deep-work scheduling, time tracking, weekly reports, and integrations.","inputs":[{"label":"email/Slack/calendar"},{"label":"calendar/task manager"},{"label":"your tools"},{"label":"your level"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","JavaScript","Python"],"est_time":"2–4 days","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Data flow**\\n```\\nEmail/Slack/Calendar → Webhooks → AI scorer (priority 1–5)\\n   → Todoist (auto-tagged)\\n   → Calendar (deep-work blocks auto-inserted Mon–Fri 09–11)\\n   → Time tracker (auto-start on focus)\\n   → Weekly report (Notion page, Sunday 18:00)\\n```\\n\\n**Scoring prompt (excerpt)**\\n> Score 1–5 on urgency, importance, and energy-fit. Output JSON: {score, reason, suggested_block}.\\n\\n**Tech:** Python + n8n + Anthropic API + Todoist + Google Calendar."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Communication","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Meeting Prep","prompt":"\\"I have a meeting about [topic] with [who].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Create an agenda\\n2. Suggest 5 key questions\\n3. Draft a follow-up email template\\n4. Create an action items tracker\\"","tags":["meetings","preparation","templates","15-minutes"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An agenda, five sharp questions, a follow-up email template, and an action-items tracker — all in 5 minutes.","inputs":[{"label":"topic"},{"label":"who"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"15 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Agenda (30 min)**\\n1. Context recap (3 min)\\n2. Decisions needed (10 min) — list 2 here\\n3. Open risks (8 min)\\n4. Next steps + owners (5 min)\\n5. Parking lot (4 min)\\n\\n**Questions to ask**\\n1. What\'s the success criterion for this in 30 days?\\n2. What\'s the blocker we\'re not naming?\\n3. Who\'s the single accountable owner?\\n4. What signal will tell us to course-correct?\\n5. What\'s the one thing we\'re optimising for?\\n\\n**Follow-up template:** Decisions / Owners / Risks / Next sync — one line each."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Communication","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Meeting Effectiveness","prompt":"\\"I attend [X] meetings/week and feel they\'re unproductive.\\n\\nPlease help me create:\\n1. Meeting criteria checklist\\n2. Agenda templates by type\\n3. Note-taking framework\\n4. Decision log template\\n5. Follow-up automation\\n\\nFocus on reducing time while improving outcomes.\\"","tags":["meetings","efficiency","templates","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A meeting-quality checklist, agenda templates by type, a note-taking framework, a decision log, and a follow-up automation plan.","inputs":[{"label":"X"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Quality checklist (run before sending the invite)**\\n- [ ] Is there a single decision or output? If not, don\'t schedule.\\n- [ ] Is the right person in the room? Limit to ≤6.\\n- [ ] Pre-read attached and read by attendees?\\n\\n**Agenda types**\\n- Decision (30 min) — context, options, decide, owner\\n- Working session (60 min) — goal, work, check-out\\n- Status (15 min) — async-first; meet only if blocked\\n\\n**Decision log columns:** Date · Decision · Owner · Rationale · Reversal cost."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Meetings & Communication","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Meeting Intelligence System","prompt":"\\"Build a meeting intelligence system that:\\n\\n1. Transcribes from [Zoom/Teams/Meet]\\n2. Extracts action items automatically\\n3. Identifies decisions\\n4. Tracks topic trends\\n5. Suggests follow-up agendas\\n6. Integrates with [project tool]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Privacy-compliant\\n- Multi-language\\n- Speaker identification\\n- Export formats\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Architecture with local Whisper + LLM\\n- Processing pipeline code\\n- UI mockups\\n- Deployment instructions\\"","tags":["ai","transcription","automation","privacy","multi-week"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A privacy-friendly transcription + extraction system: local Whisper for ASR, LLM for action items / decisions, topic trending, follow-up agenda suggestions, UI mocks.","inputs":[{"label":"Zoom/Teams/Meet"},{"label":"project tool"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nZoom recording → Local Whisper (large-v3) → Diarised transcript\\n   → LLM extractor → JSON {decisions, actions, owners, due}\\n   → Topic tracker (vector DB) → Trend dashboard\\n   → Project tool sync (Linear / Jira)\\n```\\n\\n**Sample extraction**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"actions\\": [\\n    {\\"text\\": \\"Send pricing memo to Alex\\", \\"owner\\": \\"Sam\\", \\"due\\": \\"2026-05-22\\"},\\n    {\\"text\\": \\"Spike on auth migration\\", \\"owner\\": \\"Priya\\", \\"due\\": \\"2026-05-29\\"}\\n  ],\\n  \\"decisions\\": [\\"Ship dark mode behind a flag in 1.4.0\\"]\\n}\\n```"},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Learning & Development","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"30-Day Learning Plan","prompt":"\\"I want to learn [skill]. I\'m a beginner with [X hours]/week.\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. A 30-day learning plan\\n2. Free/cheap resources\\n3. Simple practice projects\\n4. Progress tracking template\\n5. Milestones to celebrate\\"","tags":["learning","career-development","beginner","self-paced"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A 30-day learning plan, free/cheap resources, beginner-level practice projects, a progress tracker, and milestone moments.","inputs":[{"label":"skill"},{"label":"X hours"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"Self-paced","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Week 1 — Foundations**\\n- 4 × 1-hr lessons (e.g., Andrew Ng intro)\\n- Read 3 short essays, write reactions\\n- Mini project: rebuild a basic example end-to-end\\n\\n**Week 2 — Apply**\\n- Pick a small dataset / problem from your own work\\n- Ship a v0 by Friday\\n\\n**Week 3 — Stretch**\\n- Find a community (Discord/forum) and post one question\\n- Read 1 deeper paper or book chapter\\n\\n**Week 4 — Consolidate**\\n- Write a 600-word \\"what I learned\\" note\\n- Share it; ask for one critique\\n\\n**Milestones:** day 7 (first ship), day 14 (community), day 30 (public artefact)."},{"domain":"Personal Productivity","section":"Learning & Development","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Career Development Plan","prompt":"\\"I need to build expertise in [AI/data/leadership] for career progression.\\n\\nCurrent level: [describe]\\nTarget role: [describe]\\nTimeframe: [X months]\\nBudget: [X hours/week, $X]\\n\\nPlease design:\\n1. Competency map\\n2. Learning path with milestones\\n3. Project-based practice\\n4. Accountability system\\n5. Portfolio strategy\\n6. Network building plan\\n\\nOutput as a career development plan.\\"","tags":["career","upskilling","planning","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A competency map, a milestone learning path, project-based practice, an accountability system, a portfolio strategy, and a networking plan.","inputs":[{"label":"AI/data/leadership"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"X months"},{"label":"X hours/week, $X"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Competency map** (target: Senior PM, 12 months)\\n| Skill | Now | Target | Gap |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Product strategy | 3/5 | 4/5 | course + 1 case study |\\n| Stakeholder mgmt | 4/5 | 4/5 | maintain |\\n| Analytical depth | 2/5 | 4/5 | SQL + analytics cert |\\n| Influence at exec level | 2/5 | 4/5 | mentor + practice |\\n\\n**Quarter 1 plan:** SQL course, 2 user-research interviews/wk, weekly 1:1 with skip-level.\\n\\n**Portfolio:** ship 3 case studies (problem, decision, outcome) by month 9."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"UI/UX Design","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Page Layout Help","prompt":"\\"I need to design a [dashboard/form/page] for [purpose].\\n\\nUsers: [who]\\nKey actions: [list]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Suggest a layout\\n2. Recommend color scheme\\n3. List essential elements\\n4. Point out common mistakes\\n5. Suggest tools (free/low-cost)\\"","tags":["ui-design","layout","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A suggested layout, a colour scheme, an essentials list, the most common mistakes to avoid, and free tool picks.","inputs":[{"label":"dashboard/form/page"},{"label":"purpose"},{"label":"who"},{"label":"list"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Layout (dashboard, desktop-first)**\\n- Top: page title + global filter row (1 row)\\n- Left rail: nav (collapsible)\\n- Main: 3-col KPI strip → 2-col chart block → table → footer\\n\\n**Colour scheme**\\n- Bg: near-black (#0E1120)\\n- Surface: dark blue-grey (#161A2C)\\n- Primary action: violet (#9F8CFF)\\n- Positive / negative / neutral: cyan / rose / parchment\\n\\n**Common mistakes:** too many colours, busy charts, no whitespace, low contrast on labels.\\n\\n**Tools (free):** Figma, Penpot, Excalidraw."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"UI/UX Design","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Full App Design","prompt":"\\"Design a [web app/dashboard/mobile app] for [use case].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- User types: [list]\\n- Key features: [list]\\n- Must integrate with: [systems]\\n- Brand guidelines: [describe]\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. User flow diagrams\\n2. Wireframe descriptions\\n3. Component specs\\n4. Responsive considerations\\n5. Accessibility requirements\\n6. Design system recommendations\\n\\nOutput as structured documentation.\\"","tags":["ux-design","wireframes","design-system","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"User flows, wireframe descriptions, component specs, responsive considerations, a11y requirements, and a design-system recommendation.","inputs":[{"label":"web app/dashboard/mobile app"},{"label":"use case"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"systems"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Primary flow (new user)**\\n1. Sign up → email verify → onboarding tour (skippable)\\n2. Empty state → choose first task → wins (badge, confetti)\\n3. Day-2 nudge → return + retain\\n\\n**Wireframes (described)**\\n- Home: top hero, three-card empty-state, primary CTA\\n- Detail: left meta column, main content, right rail with related items\\n- Settings: 3-tab layout, sticky save bar\\n\\n**Responsive:** breakpoints 640 / 768 / 1024 / 1280; mobile uses bottom-nav, desktop uses side rail.\\n\\n**A11y:** WCAG 2.1 AA contrast, focus rings on all interactive elements, keyboard-first nav, prefers-reduced-motion respected."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"UI/UX Design","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Design System Build","prompt":"\\"Build a design system and component library for [product].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Figma/Sketch components\\n- Design tokens (colors, typography, spacing)\\n- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance\\n- Dark/light mode\\n- Multi-language\\n- Mobile-first\\n\\nTechnical:\\n- React/Vue/Angular components\\n- Storybook documentation\\n- Automated testing\\n- Version control\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Component architecture\\n- Token structure\\n- Code examples\\n- Documentation template\\n- Governance process\\"","tags":["design-system","components","accessibility","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A component architecture, token structure, code examples, documentation template, and governance process — across Figma + React + Storybook.","inputs":[{"label":"product"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Figma","JavaScript"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Token tree**\\n```\\ncolor/\\n  bg/{abyss, steel, hairline}\\n  fg/{1, 2, 3, on-violet}\\n  accent/{violet, cyan-ice}\\n  diff/{beginner, intermediate, advanced, expert}\\ntype/{display, h1, h2, body, eyebrow, mono}\\nspace/{1..24}    // 4px grid\\nradius/{none, sm, md, lg, pill}\\nshadow/{1, 2, 3, glow, glow-strong}\\nmotion/{ease-out, dur-fast, dur-base, dur-slow}\\n```\\n\\n**Governance:** all changes via PR, two reviewers (1 design + 1 eng), Storybook snapshots + visual diff CI."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Data Visualization","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Chart Selection Help","prompt":"\\"I need to create charts for [report/presentation]. Data is about [topic].\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Choose the right chart types\\n2. Describe how to make them clear\\n3. Suggest color scheme\\n4. List labels/annotations to add\\n5. Recommend tools (Excel/Google Sheets/etc.)\\"","tags":["data-viz","charts","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Chart-type picks per metric, clarity tips, a colour scheme, the labels/annotations you need, and tool suggestions.","inputs":[{"label":"report/presentation"},{"label":"topic"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel","Google Sheets"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Picks**\\n- Trend over time → line (use bands for variability)\\n- Composition → stacked bar (small categories) or treemap (≥8)\\n- Ranking → horizontal bar, longest at top\\n- Distribution → histogram or box plot\\n- Correlation → scatter, with regression line if signal is strong\\n\\n**Clarity:** start y-axis at 0 for bar charts (not always for line); label the most important point on the line, not all of them; lose the gridlines you don\'t read.\\n\\n**Colour:** one neutral + one accent. No rainbow palettes for ordinal data."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Data Visualization","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Dashboard Design","prompt":"\\"Design a dashboard for [department] tracking [KPIs].\\n\\nKPIs: [list]\\nUpdate frequency: [real-time/daily/weekly]\\nUsers: [roles]\\nDevice: [desktop/tablet/mobile]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Dashboard layout with sections\\n2. Chart type recommendations\\n3. Interaction design (filters, drill-down)\\n4. Alert/notification design\\n5. Mobile adaptation strategy\\n\\nOutput as wireframe descriptions + specs.\\"","tags":["dashboard","data-viz","kpi","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A sectioned layout, chart-type picks per KPI, interaction design (filters, drill-down), an alert/notification scheme, and a mobile adaptation plan.","inputs":[{"label":"department"},{"label":"KPIs"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"real-time/daily/weekly"},{"label":"roles"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Sections (top → bottom)**\\n1. KPI strip (4 numbers, target vs. actual)\\n2. Trend grid (4 line charts, shared x-axis)\\n3. Breakdown (1 large + 2 small)\\n4. Anomaly table (sortable, default by severity)\\n\\n**Interactions**\\n- Global filters: date range, region, segment\\n- Click a KPI tile → drill into its detail page\\n- Right-click any value → \\"explain this number\\" (LLM)\\n\\n**Mobile:** collapse to single column, hide breakdown by default behind an accordion, keep KPI strip + one trend."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Data Visualization","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Real-Time Analytics Dashboard","prompt":"\\"Build a real-time analytics dashboard using [React/Vue] + [D3/Chart.js].\\n\\nData sources:\\n- [API]\\n- [Database]\\n- [IoT sensors]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Sub-second updates\\n- Handle [X] concurrent users\\n- Custom visualizations\\n- Export capabilities\\n- Role-based access\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Frontend architecture\\n- Data pipeline design\\n- State management\\n- Performance optimization\\n- Testing strategy\\"","tags":["dashboard","real-time","frontend","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A frontend architecture, data pipeline design, state management, performance optimisations, and a testing strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"React/Vue"},{"label":"D3/Chart.js"},{"label":"API"},{"label":"Database"},{"label":"IoT sensors"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","D3","JavaScript"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Frontend**\\n- React + TanStack Query for data\\n- D3 for custom charts, Tremor for stock components\\n- State: Zustand for UI, React Query for server-state\\n\\n**Data path**\\n```\\nKafka → Pinot (OLAP) → REST/WS → React\\n                       ↳ SSE for live KPIs\\n```\\n\\n**Perf**\\n- Virtualise tables >200 rows\\n- Web workers for any chart computing >5ms\\n- LRU on dimension queries (TTL 30s)\\n\\n**Testing:** Playwright e2e for critical flows, Storybook visual regression, k6 load test (500 RPS sustained)."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Content & Branding","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Social Media Post","prompt":"\\"I need to create [X] social media posts about [topic].\\n\\nPlatform: [LinkedIn/Twitter/Instagram]\\nTone: [professional/casual/funny]\\nAudience: [describe]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Draft [X] posts\\n2. Suggest hashtags\\n3. Recommend images/graphics\\n4. Create a posting schedule\\"","tags":["content","social-media","marketing","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Ten platform-tailored draft posts, suggested hashtags, image direction, and a posting schedule.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"topic"},{"label":"LinkedIn/Twitter/Instagram"},{"label":"professional/casual/funny"},{"label":"describe"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**LinkedIn — Post 1 (educational)**\\n> Three things I\'ve stopped doing as a [role] this year:\\n> 1. Sitting in status meetings without an agenda\\n> 2. Answering \\"quick questions\\" in DM\\n> 3. Volunteering for work I don\'t own\\n> What did you stop doing? ↓\\n\\n**LinkedIn — Post 2 (POV)** [...]\\n\\n**Hashtags:** #ProductManagement #FoundersJourney (max 3–5, never on the first line)\\n\\n**Schedule:** Tue 09:00 educational, Thu 12:00 POV, Sat 10:00 story. Repurpose to Twitter same day, IG carousel on weekends."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Content & Branding","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Content Strategy","prompt":"\\"I need a content strategy for [company/product] targeting [audience].\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- Platforms: [list]\\n- Posting frequency: [describe]\\n- Engagement: [metrics]\\n\\nGoals:\\n- [Brand awareness/leads/community/etc.]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Content pillars/themes\\n2. Editorial calendar template\\n3. Content mix (educational/promotional/engaging)\\n4. Repurposing strategy\\n5. Success metrics\\n\\nOutput as a strategy document.\\"","tags":["content-strategy","marketing","editorial","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Content pillars, an editorial calendar template, a content-mix recipe, a repurposing plan, and success metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"company/product"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"metrics"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pillars (3)**\\n1. Craft — how we build (40%)\\n2. Behind the scenes — the boring middle (35%)\\n3. POV — opinionated takes that age well (25%)\\n\\n**Mix per week**\\n- 2 LinkedIn long-form\\n- 3 Twitter threads\\n- 1 newsletter\\n- 1 short video (TikTok / Reels)\\n\\n**Repurposing:** newsletter → LI thread → Twitter excerpt → reel script. One artefact, four formats.\\n\\n**Metrics:** save rate (not likes), newsletter conversion, comment-to-DM ratio."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Content & Branding","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"AI Content Engine","prompt":"\\"Build an AI-powered content generation system for [company].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Generate blog posts, social posts, emails\\n- Maintain brand voice consistency\\n- SEO optimization\\n- Multi-language support\\n- A/B testing headlines\\n- Content calendar automation\\n\\nIntegration:\\n- CMS: [WordPress/Webflow/etc.]\\n- Analytics: [Google Analytics/etc.]\\n- Social schedulers: [Buffer/Hootsuite/etc.]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Content generation pipeline\\n- Brand voice training approach\\n- Quality control process\\n- Automation workflows\\n- Performance tracking\\"","tags":["ai-content","marketing-automation","seo","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A generation pipeline, brand-voice tuning approach, quality control, automation workflows, and a performance tracking system.","inputs":[{"label":"company"},{"label":"WordPress/Webflow/etc."},{"label":"Google Analytics/etc."},{"label":"Buffer/Hootsuite/etc."}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nTopic queue → Outline LLM → Section drafts (parallel)\\n   → Brand-voice critic (LLM with rubric)\\n   → SEO optimiser (keyword density, headings)\\n   → Human review (5-min sanity check)\\n   → CMS publish → Schedule social\\n```\\n\\n**Voice tuning:** 30 best-of corpus samples in an Anthropic file; system prompt anchors tone, banned words, sentence rhythm.\\n\\n**A/B headlines:** generate 5 variants per post; rotate top-2 in social; declare winner after 72 hrs.\\n\\n**Tracking:** scroll depth, time-on-page, conversion to newsletter, share rate."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Automation & Scripting","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Repetitive Task Elimination","prompt":"\\"I do repetitive [data entry/reporting/formatting] using [Excel/manual work].\\n\\nTask: [describe step by step]\\nTime: [X hours/week]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Identify if this can be automated\\n2. Suggest the easiest approach\\n3. Provide step-by-step instructions\\n4. Write simple formulas/scripts\\n5. Teach me how to maintain it\\"","tags":["automation","excel","beginner","quick-win","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A yes/no on whether it\'s automatable, the easiest path, step-by-step instructions, formulas/scripts, and a maintenance guide.","inputs":[{"label":"data entry/reporting/formatting"},{"label":"Excel/manual work"},{"label":"describe step by step"},{"label":"X hours/week"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Verdict:** automatable in under 30 minutes.\\n\\n**Simplest path:** Excel formulas + Power Query — no macros, no Python.\\n\\n**Steps**\\n1. Save your source files in one folder, e.g. `~/Reports`.\\n2. Open Excel → Data → Get Data → From Folder → point to that folder.\\n3. Power Query stitches them. Click \\"Combine & Transform\\".\\n4. Sheet auto-refreshes when files are added.\\n\\n**Formula to replace your VLOOKUP chain:**\\n```\\n=XLOOKUP(A2, LookupTable[Key], LookupTable[Value], \\"—\\", 0)\\n```\\n\\n**Maintenance:** check column names monthly; if a source file renames a column, Power Query will flag it."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Automation & Scripting","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Python Automation","prompt":"\\"I want to automate [process] using Python.\\n\\nCurrent process:\\n1. [Step 1]\\n2. [Step 2]\\n3. [Step 3]\\n\\nInputs: [file types, locations]\\nOutputs: [what you need]\\nFrequency: [daily/weekly/monthly]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Run on [Windows/Mac/Server]\\n- Error handling\\n- Notifications\\n- Logging\\n- Easy to modify\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Python script with comments\\n2. Setup instructions\\n3. Error handling\\n4. Scheduling (cron/Task Scheduler)\\n5. Documentation template\\"","tags":["python","automation","scripting","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A commented Python script, setup instructions, error handling, scheduling guidance, and a documentation template.","inputs":[{"label":"process"},{"label":"Step 1"},{"label":"Step 2"},{"label":"Step 3"},{"label":"file types, locations"}],"tools":["Claude","Python"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Script skeleton**\\n```python\\nimport logging, schedule, time\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\nlog = logging.getLogger(\\"autoreport\\")\\n\\ndef run() -> None:\\n    try:\\n        df = ingest(Path(\\"~/inputs\\").expanduser())\\n        cleaned = clean(df)\\n        save(cleaned, Path(\\"~/out\\") / \\"report.xlsx\\")\\n        notify(\\"OK\\")\\n    except Exception:\\n        log.exception(\\"run failed\\")\\n        notify(\\"FAIL\\")\\n\\nschedule.every().day.at(\\"06:00\\").do(run)\\nwhile True: schedule.run_pending(); time.sleep(60)\\n```\\n\\n**Setup:** `pipx install pdm`; `pdm add pandas openpyxl schedule`; cron entry on Mac/Linux or Task Scheduler on Windows."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Automation & Scripting","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automation Platform","prompt":"\\"Build a production-grade automation platform for [department].\\n\\nUse cases:\\n- [List 3-5]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Microservices architecture\\n- Event-driven processing\\n- Error handling + retry\\n- Monitoring and alerting\\n- Audit trail\\n- Scalable to [X] jobs/day\\n\\nTech preferences:\\n- Language: [Python/Node/Go]\\n- Infrastructure: [AWS/Azure/on-prem]\\n- Orchestration: [Airflow/Prefect/custom]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Core service code\\n- Database schema\\n- Deployment pipeline\\n- Monitoring setup\\n- Disaster recovery\\"","tags":["platform","microservices","devops","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A microservices architecture, core service skeleton, DB schema, deployment pipeline, monitoring setup, and DR plan.","inputs":[{"label":"department"},{"label":"List 3-5"},{"label":"X"},{"label":"Python/Node/Go"},{"label":"AWS/Azure/on-prem"}],"tools":["Airflow","ChatGPT","Claude","Python"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nEvent bus (NATS) ↔ Orchestrator (Prefect)\\n                   ↔ Workers (FastAPI, autoscaled)\\n                   ↔ Postgres (state) · S3 (artefacts) · Redis (cache)\\n                   ↔ Observability (OTel → Grafana)\\n```\\n\\n**Job table**\\n```sql\\ncreate table jobs (\\n  id uuid primary key,\\n  kind text not null,\\n  payload jsonb,\\n  status text check (status in (\'queued\',\'running\',\'done\',\'failed\')),\\n  attempts int default 0,\\n  created_at timestamptz default now()\\n);\\n```\\n\\n**DR:** RPO 15 min (WAL streaming), RTO 30 min (warm standby), monthly restore drills."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Data Engineering","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Data Cleaning","prompt":"\\"I have [Excel/CSV] data that I need to clean and analyze.\\n\\nData description: [columns, size]\\nProblems: [duplicates, missing values, format issues]\\nGoal: [analysis/report]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Write Python/Pandas code to clean it\\n2. Show me how to explore the data\\n3. Create basic visualizations\\n4. Export clean data\\"","tags":["data-engineering","python","pandas","beginner","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Pandas code to clean the data, exploration snippets, simple visualisations, and a clean export.","inputs":[{"label":"Excel/CSV"},{"label":"columns, size"},{"label":"duplicates, missing values, format issues"},{"label":"analysis/report"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Excel","Python"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Clean**\\n```python\\nimport pandas as pd\\ndf = pd.read_csv(\\"raw.csv\\")\\n\\ndf = (\\n    df.drop_duplicates()\\n      .assign(date=lambda d: pd.to_datetime(d[\\"date\\"], errors=\\"coerce\\"))\\n      .dropna(subset=[\\"date\\", \\"amount\\"])\\n      .query(\\"amount.abs() < 1e7\\")  # outliers\\n)\\n\\ndf[\\"amount\\"] = df[\\"amount\\"].astype(float).round(2)\\ndf.to_csv(\\"clean.csv\\", index=False)\\n```\\n\\n**Explore**\\n```python\\ndf.describe(); df.isna().sum(); df.groupby(\\"region\\")[\\"amount\\"].sum().plot.bar()\\n```"},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Data Engineering","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Data Pipeline","prompt":"\\"Design a data pipeline for [use case].\\n\\nSources:\\n- [ERP/SAP/Salesforce]\\n- [CRM data]\\n- [External data]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Daily refresh\\n- Historical tracking\\n- Data quality checks\\n- Access for [X] users\\n- Budget: [range]\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Pipeline architecture\\n2. ETL/ELT approach\\n3. Data model design\\n4. Quality checks\\n5. Documentation standards\\n6. Tool recommendations\\"","tags":["data-pipeline","etl","data-modeling","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A pipeline architecture, ETL/ELT approach, data model, quality checks, documentation standards, and tool picks.","inputs":[{"label":"use case"},{"label":"ERP/SAP/Salesforce"},{"label":"CRM data"},{"label":"External data"},{"label":"X"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture (ELT)**\\n```\\nSources (SAP, Salesforce, files)\\n  → Fivetran / Airbyte (ingest)\\n  → Snowflake raw schema\\n  → dbt models (staging → marts)\\n  → Great Expectations (tests)\\n  → BI (Power BI / Looker)\\n```\\n\\n**Marts**\\n- `mart_finance.fct_invoice` — grain = invoice line\\n- `mart_finance.dim_customer` — SCD type 2\\n\\n**Quality (per run)**\\n- Row count vs. prior run (alert if >5% drift)\\n- Null %, distinct count\\n- Joinable to dim tables = 100%"},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"Data Engineering","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Modern Data Platform","prompt":"\\"Build a modern data platform.\\n\\nScale:\\n- [X] TB data\\n- [X] sources\\n- [X] users\\n- [X] queries/day\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Real-time and batch processing\\n- Data catalog\\n- Lineage tracking\\n- Quality monitoring\\n- Cost optimization\\n- GDPR compliance\\n- Self-service analytics\\n\\nTech preferences: [open to suggestions]\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Platform architecture\\n- Component selection\\n- Implementation phases\\n- Team structure\\n- Cost estimates\\n- Migration strategy\\"","tags":["data-platform","architecture","multi-week","enterprise"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A platform architecture, tool selection, phased rollout, team structure, cost estimate, and migration strategy.","inputs":[{"label":"X"},{"label":"open to suggestions"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Architecture**\\n```\\nIngest: Fivetran + Kafka\\nStore: Snowflake (warehouse) + Iceberg (lake)\\nTransform: dbt\\nCatalog: DataHub\\nQuality: Great Expectations\\nReverse-ETL: Hightouch\\nBI: Looker (semantic) + Power BI (long tail)\\n```\\n\\n**Team (yr 1):** 1 lead, 2 analytics engineers, 1 data eng, 1 platform eng, 0.5 PM.\\n\\n**Cost (annual run-rate):** $480k software, $1.1M people = $1.6M.\\n\\n**Migration:** strangler-fig; new pipelines on platform from day 1, legacy decommission over 18 mo."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI/ML Applications","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"AI Feasibility Check","prompt":"\\"I want to use AI to help with [specific task].\\n\\nWhat I have:\\n- [Data description]\\n- [Problem description]\\n- [Current process]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Explain if AI is appropriate\\n2. Suggest the simplest approach\\n3. List what data I need\\n4. Recommend tools (no-code/low-code)\\n5. Estimate effort and accuracy\\"","tags":["ai","feasibility","beginner","consulting","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An honest take on whether AI fits, the simplest approach, data requirements, no-code/low-code tools, and an effort/accuracy estimate.","inputs":[{"label":"specific task"},{"label":"Data description"},{"label":"Problem description"},{"label":"Current process"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**Fit check:** YES — but use rules + LLM, not ML from scratch. Your data shape (text + categories) is ideal for LLM classification with few-shot examples.\\n\\n**Simplest path**\\n1. 20–50 hand-labelled examples\\n2. Prompt with examples + output schema\\n3. Run in batch (Make.com / Zapier scheduled)\\n\\n**Effort:** ~2 hours setup, ~$5–20/month in LLM cost.\\n\\n**Expected accuracy:** 88–94% on the obvious cases; design a fallback for the 6–12% it gets wrong."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI/ML Applications","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"ML Model Build","prompt":"\\"Build an ML model for [demand forecasting/churn/etc.].\\n\\nData:\\n- Historical data: [time range, granularity]\\n- Features: [list]\\n- Target: [what to predict]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Retrain monthly\\n- Explain predictions\\n- Confidence intervals\\n- Deploy to [environment]\\n- Monitor drift\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n1. Data preparation pipeline\\n2. Model selection and training\\n3. Evaluation framework\\n4. Deployment approach\\n5. Monitoring setup\\n6. Business metrics\\"","tags":["machine-learning","modeling","deployment","half-day-to-week"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A data prep pipeline, model selection + training, evaluation framework, deployment approach, monitoring setup, and business metrics.","inputs":[{"label":"demand forecasting/churn/etc."},{"label":"time range, granularity"},{"label":"list"},{"label":"what to predict"},{"label":"environment"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day – 1 week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nRaw → feature store (Feast)\\n   → training (XGBoost + LightGBM ensemble)\\n   → eval (MAPE, prediction interval coverage)\\n   → registry (MLflow)\\n   → serving (FastAPI / Triton)\\n   → monitoring (Evidently)\\n```\\n\\n**Eval (forecasting)**\\n- MAPE: target ≤8% at SKU-week grain\\n- 80% prediction interval coverage ≥75%\\n- Bias drift week-over-week ≤2pp\\n\\n**Business metrics:** stockout rate (↓ target 35%), overstock cost (↓ target $1.2M/yr)."},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI/ML Applications","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Enterprise ML Platform","prompt":"\\"Design an enterprise AI/ML platform.\\n\\nUse cases across departments:\\n- Demand forecasting\\n- Customer segmentation\\n- Predictive maintenance\\n- Quality control\\n- Pricing optimization\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- MLOps lifecycle\\n- Feature store\\n- Experiment tracking\\n- Model registry\\n- A/B testing\\n- Monitoring\\n- Governance\\n- Multi-cloud\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Platform architecture\\n- Component selection\\n- Implementation roadmap\\n- Team and skills needed\\n- Cost model\\n- Success metrics\\"","tags":["mlops","enterprise","platform","multi-month","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A multi-cloud MLOps platform: architecture, components, rollout roadmap, team plan, cost model, and metrics.","inputs":[],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-month","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Stack**\\n- Feature store: Feast\\n- Experiment tracking: Weights & Biases\\n- Registry + serving: MLflow + KServe\\n- Orchestration: Argo Workflows\\n- Monitoring: Evidently + Prometheus + Grafana\\n- Governance: model card per release, signed by data steward\\n\\n**Rollout (12 mo)**\\n- Q1: foundation (registry, serving, baseline monitoring)\\n- Q2: first two production models (forecasting, churn)\\n- Q3: feature store, A/B framework\\n- Q4: governance, audit, multi-cloud failover\\n\\n**TCO yr 1:** $1.8–2.4M."},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Market Research","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Quick Market Scan","prompt":"\\"I need a quick overview of [market/industry].\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. List top 5 players\\n2. Describe market size and growth\\n3. Identify key trends\\n4. Note any recent news/developments\\n5. Suggest 3 sources to read deeper\\"","tags":["market-research","overview","quick-scan","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Top five players, market size + growth, key trends, recent news, and three deeper sources.","inputs":[{"label":"market/industry"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Top players** (mention only — sample shape, not real data)\\n1. Player A — incumbent, ~38% share, slow product velocity\\n2. Player B — pricing leader, growing in SMB\\n3. Player C — design-led challenger, last raised $80M\\n4. Player D — open-source play, strong dev community\\n5. Player E — vertical specialist (healthcare)\\n\\n**Market:** ~$8.4B, CAGR 14%, fragmenting toward verticals.\\n\\n**Trends:** consolidation in core, vertical land-grabs, AI-overlay pricing power.\\n\\n**Read deeper:** [Gartner MQ] · [a16z thesis] · [recent Stratechery piece]."},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Market Research","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Deep Dive Report","prompt":"\\"I need a comprehensive market analysis of [industry] for [purpose].\\n\\nFocus areas:\\n- Market size and forecast\\n- Competitive landscape\\n- Customer segments\\n- Technology trends\\n- Regulatory environment\\n- Entry barriers\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Executive summary\\n2. Market structure analysis\\n3. Competitor profiles (top 5)\\n4. Trend analysis\\n5. Opportunity assessment\\n6. Risk factors\\n7. Recommendations\\n\\nOutput as a professional report.\\"","tags":["market-research","report","strategy","half-day-to-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A full market analysis: exec summary, structure, top-5 competitor profiles, trends, opportunities, risks, and recommendations.","inputs":[{"label":"industry"},{"label":"purpose"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day – 1 day","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Executive summary**\\n- Market: $12.4B, growing 11% CAGR\\n- Top-3 control 54%; long tail of 200+ players\\n- The decisive shift is from horizontal SaaS to vertical AI; budget will follow the workflow, not the tool\\n\\n**Competitor profiles** (sample of one)\\n> **Player A** — Founded 2014, ~$320M ARR. Strengths: brand + channel. Weaknesses: legacy data model, slow on AI. Strategic moves: hired ex-Snowflake CRO, opened London office. Threat to us: medium — they\'re 18 months behind on AI but have the customer base.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** focus enterprise GTM on three verticals where AI maturity differential is widest."},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Competitive Intelligence","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Competitor Profile","prompt":"\\"Create a detailed profile of [competitor company].\\n\\nInclude:\\n1. Company overview (size, history, ownership)\\n2. Product/service portfolio\\n3. Pricing strategy\\n4. Market position\\n5. Strengths and weaknesses\\n6. Recent strategic moves\\n7. Financial health (if public)\\n8. Threat level to us\\n\\nFormat as an intelligence brief.\\"","tags":["competitive-intel","profiling","strategy","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A complete intelligence brief: company overview, portfolio, pricing, position, strengths/weaknesses, recent moves, financials, and threat level.","inputs":[{"label":"competitor company"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"plan","sample_output":"**Overview** — Founded 2017. ~620 FTEs. PE-backed (Series D, last priced 2024). HQ Austin, eng team in Krakow.\\n\\n**Portfolio:** one flagship product, three adjacent SKUs (analytics, audit, compliance).\\n\\n**Pricing:** $99 / $249 / Enterprise (call). 14-day trial, no card.\\n\\n**Strengths:** integrations breadth, partner channel.\\n**Weaknesses:** product velocity (~6 releases/yr), thin data-science chops.\\n\\n**Recent moves:** acquired a 12-person ML team (Q2), launched a free tier (Q3).\\n\\n**Threat level:** HIGH on SMB segment, LOW on enterprise."},{"domain":"Research & Analysis","section":"Competitive Intelligence","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Competitive Monitoring System","prompt":"\\"Build an automated competitive intelligence system that tracks:\\n\\n1. Competitor website changes\\n2. Pricing updates\\n3. New product launches\\n4. Job postings (hiring signals)\\n5. Patent filings\\n6. Social media sentiment\\n7. Review trends\\n\\nAlerts:\\n- Daily digest for minor changes\\n- Immediate alert for major changes\\n\\nDeliverables:\\n- Weekly competitive brief\\n- Monthly strategic assessment\\n- Quarterly trend report\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Data sources and APIs\\n- Scraping infrastructure\\n- Analysis pipeline\\n- Alert system\\n- Report templates\\"","tags":["competitive-intel","automation","monitoring","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An automated CI system spec: data sources, scraping infrastructure, analysis pipeline, alerts, and report templates.","inputs":[],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Sources**\\n- Website diff: weekly snapshot, HTML diff with semantic noise filter\\n- Pricing pages: daily check (specific selectors)\\n- Job boards: Greenhouse/Lever scrape + keyword classifier\\n- Patents: USPTO RSS by competitor name\\n- Reviews: G2 / Capterra weekly pull\\n\\n**Pipeline**\\n```\\nSource → Raw store (S3) → Classifier (LLM)\\n   → Significance scorer → Slack / Email\\n```\\n\\n**Alerts:** major change = pricing ±5%, exec hire, M&A rumour, raise announcement.\\n\\n**Weekly brief:** auto-generated Notion page Fri 09:00."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Process Documentation","prompt":"\\"I need to document how to [task/process].\\n\\nAudience: [new hires/team/customers]\\nCurrent knowledge: [tribal/exists in heads]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Create a step-by-step guide\\n2. Add screenshots/checkpoints\\n3. Include troubleshooting section\\n4. Make it scannable (bullet points)\\n5. Suggest where to store it\\"","tags":["documentation","process","knowledge-management","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A step-by-step guide with checkpoints, a troubleshooting section, a scannable format, and a storage recommendation.","inputs":[{"label":"task/process"},{"label":"new hires/team/customers"},{"label":"tribal/exists in heads"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Doc structure**\\n1. Who this is for (1 line)\\n2. Prerequisites (3–5 bullets)\\n3. Steps (numbered, screenshot every 3rd)\\n4. Verification checklist\\n5. Troubleshooting (top 5 issues)\\n6. Glossary\\n7. Last updated + owner\\n\\n**Tone:** imperative, second person — \\"Open the file\\" not \\"The user opens the file\\".\\n\\n**Where to store:** if it\'s product → docs site (Mintlify); if it\'s internal → Notion (one page per process, linked from a process index)."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Technical Documentation","prompt":"\\"I need technical documentation for [system/feature].\\n\\nAudience: [developers/users/administrators]\\nCurrent state: [no docs/outdated/fragmented]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Overview and architecture\\n2. Setup/installation guide\\n3. API reference (if applicable)\\n4. Usage examples\\n5. Troubleshooting guide\\n6. FAQ\\n7. Changelog template\\n\\nFormat: [Markdown/Confluence/Notion]\\"","tags":["technical-writing","documentation","developer-experience","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A complete tech doc set: overview + architecture, setup, API reference, examples, troubleshooting, FAQ, and changelog template — Markdown-ready.","inputs":[{"label":"system/feature"},{"label":"developers/users/administrators"},{"label":"no docs/outdated/fragmented"},{"label":"Markdown/Confluence/Notion"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Skeleton**\\n```\\ndocs/\\n  README.md          # overview + diagram\\n  install.md         # platforms, prerequisites\\n  api/\\n    endpoints.md     # generated from OpenAPI\\n    auth.md\\n  examples/\\n    quickstart.md\\n    advanced.md\\n  troubleshooting.md\\n  faq.md\\n  changelog.md\\n```\\n\\n**API reference (sample entry)**\\n```\\n### POST /v1/jobs\\nCreate a new job. Idempotent on `Idempotency-Key` header.\\n\\n**Body:** { kind: string, payload: object }\\n**Returns:** 201 + { id, status_url }\\n**Errors:** 400 (invalid kind), 409 (duplicate key)\\n```"},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Documentation","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Documentation Platform","prompt":"\\"Design a documentation strategy and platform for [company/product].\\n\\nCurrent state:\\n- [Scattered/outdated/non-existent]\\n- Tools: [if any]\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Version control\\n- Search functionality\\n- Multi-format output (web/PDF)\\n- Contribution workflow\\n- Review process\\n- Analytics (what\'s read, what\'s not)\\n- Integration with support tickets\\n\\nPlease provide:\\n- Information architecture\\n- Tool selection and setup\\n- Writing standards/style guide\\n- Maintenance process\\n- Migration plan (if needed)\\"","tags":["documentation","platform","knowledge-management","multi-week"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An info architecture, tool selection + setup, writing standards, maintenance process, and migration plan.","inputs":[{"label":"company/product"},{"label":"Scattered/outdated/non-existent"},{"label":"if any"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"code","sample_output":"**IA (3 trees)**\\n1. Get started (onboarding) — < 5 min reads\\n2. How-to (task-oriented) — recipe format\\n3. Reference (deep) — searchable, structured\\n\\n**Stack:** Mintlify / Docusaurus → GitHub → Vercel · Algolia search · Plausible analytics.\\n\\n**Standards**\\n- Active voice, second person\\n- Sentence case headings\\n- Every page: who-it\'s-for + outcome at top\\n- Code blocks always copy-pasteable, no shell prompts\\n\\n**Maintenance:** quarterly stale-page sweep; PR template enforces the standard."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Presentations","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Slide Content","prompt":"\\"I need to create a presentation about [topic] for [audience].\\n\\nDuration: [X minutes]\\nKey message: [one sentence]\\nData: [what you have]\\n\\nPlease:\\n1. Create an outline (title + 3-5 sections)\\n2. Write speaker notes\\n3. Suggest visuals/charts\\n4. Recommend slide count\\n5. Provide opening and closing statements\\"","tags":["presentation","slides","storytelling","1-hour"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A title + 3–5 section outline, speaker notes, suggested visuals/charts, a recommended slide count, and opening + closing statements.","inputs":[{"label":"topic"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"X minutes"},{"label":"one sentence"},{"label":"what you have"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"1 hour","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Outline (15 min)**\\n- Title — \\"Why we should bet on X\\"\\n- Section 1 — The shift (3 slides, 4 min)\\n- Section 2 — Our position (2 slides, 3 min)\\n- Section 3 — The wedge (3 slides, 5 min)\\n- Section 4 — Ask (1 slide, 2 min)\\n- Q&A (1 min)\\n\\n**Open:** \\"I\'m asking for one decision today, and I\'ll get to it in 12 minutes.\\"\\n\\n**Close:** \\"If we approve this, here\'s what we\'re doing next week. If we don\'t, here\'s what we\'ll regret.\\"\\n\\n**Recommended:** 10 slides. Less is more."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Presentations","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Presentation Design","prompt":"\\"Design a compelling presentation for [purpose].\\n\\nContext:\\n- Audience: [describe]\\n- Stake in outcome: [what they care about]\\n- Time: [X minutes]\\n- Format: [in-person/remote]\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Narrative arc (beginning, middle, end)\\n2. Slide-by-slide storyboard\\n3. Data visualization recommendations\\n4. Speaker notes with timing\\n5. Q&A preparation (anticipate 5 questions)\\n6. Handout design\\n\\nMake it persuasive, not just informative.\\"","tags":["presentation","design","storytelling","persuasion","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A narrative arc, storyboard, viz recommendations, timed speaker notes, anticipated Q&A, and a handout.","inputs":[{"label":"purpose"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"what they care about"},{"label":"X minutes"},{"label":"in-person/remote"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Arc**\\n1. Setup — the world they know\\n2. Disruption — what\'s changed\\n3. Resolution — what we do about it\\n4. Ask — the decision\\n\\n**Speaker notes (slide 4)**\\n> \\"Three numbers tell this story. The first is [X] — that\'s our baseline. The second is [Y] — that\'s the new reality. The third is [Z] — that\'s the gap we have to close.\\"\\n\\n**Anticipated Q1:** \\"Why now, not next year?\\" — A: 2-sentence answer + back-up slide ready.\\n\\n**Handout:** 2-pager, exec summary front, FAQ back."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Presentations","skill_level":"ADVANCED","skill_emoji":"🟢","title":"Automated Presentation Generation","prompt":"\\"Build a system that generates presentations from [data source].\\n\\nRequirements:\\n- Pull data from [database/API/spreadsheet]\\n- Auto-generate charts and visuals\\n- Apply brand template\\n- Create narrative from data insights\\n- Export to PowerPoint/Google Slides\\n- Schedule automatic updates\\n\\nUse cases:\\n- Monthly board reports\\n- Weekly sales updates\\n- Quarterly business reviews\\n\\nProvide:\\n- System architecture\\n- Template design system\\n- Data-to-slide mapping\\n- Automation pipeline\\n- Quality checks\\"","tags":["presentation","automation","data-to-slides","multi-week","production"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"An end-to-end data-to-deck system: architecture, template design, data-to-slide mapping, automation pipeline, and quality checks.","inputs":[{"label":"data source"},{"label":"database/API/spreadsheet"}],"tools":["ChatGPT","Claude","Excel"],"est_time":"Multi-week","output_kind":"visual","sample_output":"**Pipeline**\\n```\\nSources → SQL → DataFrame\\n   → Template engine (python-pptx + branded slide masters)\\n   → Narrative generator (LLM with structured prompt per slide)\\n   → QA pass (LLM critic + rule-based checks)\\n   → S3 + Slack delivery\\n```\\n\\n**Slide mapping**\\n| Slide | Data query | Layout |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| 1 — Headline | revenue_summary.sql | KPI tile |\\n| 2 — Trend | revenue_monthly.sql | line chart |\\n| 3 — Variance | budget_var.sql | table + comment |\\n\\n**QA:** every number must trace to a query hash; LLM critic checks for tone + cross-slide consistency."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Email & Communication","skill_level":"BEGINNER","skill_emoji":"🔴","title":"Email Templates","prompt":"\\"I need email templates for [situation].\\n\\nPlease create:\\n1. Initial outreach\\n2. Follow-up after no response\\n3. Meeting request\\n4. Thank you after meeting\\n5. Status update\\n\\nTone: [professional/friendly/urgent]\\nKeep them short and actionable.\\"","tags":["email","templates","communication","30-minutes"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"Five reusable templates — initial outreach, follow-up, meeting request, thank-you, status update — short and actionable.","inputs":[{"label":"situation"},{"label":"professional/friendly/urgent"}],"tools":["ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 min","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Initial outreach**\\n> Subject: [their company] × [your company] — quick idea\\n> Hi [name], saw [specific signal]. We help [people like them] do [specific outcome]. Worth a 15-min chat next week?\\n\\n**Follow-up (after no reply)**\\n> Subject: bumping this up\\n> Hi [name], jumping back here. If now\'s a bad week, just let me know and I\'ll try again in [month].\\n\\n**Meeting request**\\n> Subject: 20 min, [topic]?\\n> Goal: decide [X]. Tue 10am, Thu 2pm — what works?\\n\\n**Thank-you**\\n> Thanks for the time. Three things I owe you: [...]. Talk [date].\\n\\n**Status update**\\n> [Project] · [colour] · [1-line headline]. Wins: [...]. Risks: [...]. Asks: [...]."},{"domain":"Communication & Writing","section":"Email & Communication","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","skill_emoji":"🟡","title":"Communication Strategy","prompt":"\\"I need to communicate [change/decision/update] to [audience].\\n\\nContext:\\n- What\'s changing: [describe]\\n- Why: [reason]\\n- Impact: [who\'s affected and how]\\n- Timeline: [when]\\n- Concerns: [what people will worry about]\\n\\nPlease help me:\\n1. Craft the core message\\n2. Create an FAQ (10 questions)\\n3. Design a communication timeline\\n4. Write for different channels (email, meeting, doc)\\n5. Plan for feedback and resistance\\n6. Create a feedback loop\\"","tags":["communication","change-management","strategy","half-day"],"best_for":"","source":"","outcome":"A core message, a 10-question FAQ, a comms timeline, channel-specific drafts, a resistance plan, and a feedback loop design.","inputs":[{"label":"change/decision/update"},{"label":"audience"},{"label":"describe"},{"label":"reason"},{"label":"who\'s affected and how"}],"tools":["Claude"],"est_time":"Half day","output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Core message** (1 sentence)\\n> \\"We\'re moving [process] to [new tool] over the next 8 weeks so [outcome] — and we\'re keeping [thing they care about] exactly as it is.\\"\\n\\n**FAQ (sample 3 of 10)**\\n- Q: Why now? A: [specific reason + signal]\\n- Q: What changes for me? A: [day-1 impact, week-1 impact]\\n- Q: What if I disagree? A: [exact path + when]\\n\\n**Timeline**\\n- Week 0: leader pre-brief\\n- Week 1: all-hands announcement + FAQ doc\\n- Week 2: 1:1s for top concerns\\n- Week 4: midpoint pulse survey\\n- Week 8: retro\\n\\n**Feedback loop:** anonymous form + biweekly office hours; ship one visible change in response."},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Explain Anything in Plain English","prompt":"Explain [concept or topic] to me as if I have no background in it. Use an analogy, give me the 3 key things I need to know, and tell me what I can ignore for now.","tags":["learning","explainer","beginner","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants to understand something fast","outcome":"A jargon-free explanation with an analogy and the three things that actually matter.","inputs":[{"label":"concept or topic"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**The concept:** Kubernetes\\n\\n**Analogy:** Think of your apps like shipping containers. Kubernetes is the shipping port — it decides which ships (servers) carry which containers, automatically reroutes if a ship has problems, and scales up when demand surges.\\n\\n**3 things you need to know:**\\n1. It auto-heals: if your app crashes, Kubernetes restarts it\\n2. It scales: add more traffic, it adds more instances automatically\\n3. It abstracts infrastructure: you describe *what* you want, not *where* it runs\\n\\n**You can ignore for now:** etcd, control plane internals, CNI plugins — those are ops concerns unless you\'re running the cluster yourself."},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Summarise Any Document or Article","prompt":"Summarise the following [document type] in 5 bullet points. Highlight the single most important takeaway, flag any risks or open questions, and note one action I could take today.\\n\\n[paste content]","tags":["summary","reading","quick","productivity"],"best_for":"Anyone who reads a lot and needs the key points fast","outcome":"5-bullet summary with the top insight, risks flagged, and one concrete action.","inputs":[{"label":"document type"},{"label":"paste content"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Summary: Q3 Investor Update**\\n\\n- Revenue hit $4.2M ARR (+18% QoQ) driven by enterprise expansion, not new logos\\n- Churn ticked up to 3.2% — two large accounts left citing \\"missing integrations\\"\\n- Hiring plan is 6 engineers by year-end; currently 2 offers outstanding\\n- Runway is 22 months at current burn; Series B target is Q1 next year\\n- Product roadmap: API v2 is the top priority for Q4\\n\\n**Most important takeaway:** Growth is healthy but churn signal on integrations needs immediate product response.\\n\\n**Risk:** If the two outstanding offers don\'t close, engineering plan slips and API v2 is at risk.\\n\\n**Action today:** Schedule a 30-min call with the two churned accounts to validate the integration gap before roadmap is locked."},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Rewrite This More Clearly","prompt":"Rewrite the following text to be clearer and more direct. Remove jargon, shorten sentences, and keep the core meaning intact. Also give me one sentence explaining the main change you made.\\n\\n[paste text]","tags":["editing","clarity","writing","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who wants to communicate more clearly","outcome":"A polished, plain-English rewrite plus a one-line explanation of the key edit.","inputs":[{"label":"paste text"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**Original:** \\"In order to facilitate the optimisation of our cross-functional synergy initiatives, we will be leveraging a new paradigm of collaborative frameworks going forward.\\"\\n\\n**Rewritten:** \\"We\'re rolling out a new approach to help teams work together better.\\"\\n\\n**Main change:** Removed every piece of corporate jargon and cut from 27 words to 11 without losing meaning."},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Draft a Quick Reply Email","prompt":"Write a brief email reply to the following message. Keep it under 80 words, be friendly but professional, answer the key question directly, and end with a clear next step.\\n\\n[paste the email you received]","tags":["email","communication","quick","writing"],"best_for":"Anyone with a full inbox who wants to reply faster","outcome":"A concise, professional reply under 80 words with a clear next step.","inputs":[{"label":"paste the email you received"}],"tools":["Claude","Gmail","Outlook"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"Hi Sarah,\\n\\nThanks for reaching out — yes, we can move the Thursday call to 3 PM instead of 2 PM. Works perfectly.\\n\\nI\'ll send a revised invite now. Looking forward to walking through the Q4 plan with you.\\n\\nBest,\\nAlex"},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Turn Meeting Notes into Action Items","prompt":"I have rough notes from a meeting. Extract all action items in a clean table with: Owner, Action, Deadline (if mentioned). Then write a 2-sentence meeting summary I can paste into Slack.\\n\\nNotes: [paste meeting notes]","tags":["meetings","productivity","notes","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who takes meeting notes and needs to distribute them fast","outcome":"Structured action item table + a 2-sentence Slack-ready summary.","inputs":[{"label":"paste meeting notes"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Slack"],"output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Action Items**\\n\\n| Owner | Action | Deadline |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Priya | Send revised pricing deck to enterprise accounts | Friday EOD |\\n| Marcus | Book venue for Q4 kickoff | Next Wednesday |\\n| Team | Review updated OKRs before next sync | Thursday AM |\\n\\n**Slack summary:**\\nWe aligned on Q4 priorities — pricing update and venue booking are the two blockers. Full action list in Notion."},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Generate a Pro/Con List","prompt":"I need to decide between [option A] and [option B] in the context of [your situation]. Give me a structured pro/con table for each, weight the most important factors, and give me your recommendation with a one-sentence rationale.","tags":["decision-making","planning","quick","analysis"],"best_for":"Anyone facing a decision who wants a structured view fast","outcome":"A weighted pro/con table for both options plus a clear recommendation.","inputs":[{"label":"option A"},{"label":"option B"},{"label":"your situation"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"table","sample_output":"**Option A: Hire a full-time designer**\\n\\n| Pro | Con |\\n|---|---|\\n| Deep brand consistency | 3-month ramp time |\\n| Embedded in team | $90k+ cost |\\n| Long-term asset | Risk if workload drops |\\n\\n**Option B: Use a design agency**\\n\\n| Pro | Con |\\n|---|---|\\n| Fast start (1–2 weeks) | Less brand ownership |\\n| Flexible scope | Higher per-hour cost |\\n| No hiring risk | Communication overhead |\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Start with the agency. Your product roadmap is still shifting — locking in a full-time hire before the design direction is settled is premature."},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Create a Template from a One-Off Doc","prompt":"Turn the following one-off document into a reusable template. Replace specific names, dates, and numbers with clear [PLACEHOLDER] labels. Add a short instruction comment above each placeholder explaining what to fill in.\\n\\n[paste document]","tags":["templates","documentation","reuse","quick"],"best_for":"Anyone who writes the same type of document repeatedly","outcome":"A clean, labelled template with placeholder instructions ready to reuse.","inputs":[{"label":"paste document"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Google Docs"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**PROJECT KICKOFF BRIEF**\\n\\n<!-- Project name: e.g. \\"Website Redesign Q1\\" -->\\n**Project:** [PROJECT NAME]\\n\\n<!-- One sentence describing the goal -->\\n**Objective:** [PROJECT OBJECTIVE]\\n\\n<!-- Format: Month DD, YYYY -->\\n**Launch date:** [TARGET LAUNCH DATE]\\n\\n<!-- List 2-4 people and their role -->\\n**Team:**\\n- [NAME] — [ROLE]\\n- [NAME] — [ROLE]\\n\\n<!-- What does success look like? List 2-3 measurable outcomes -->\\n**Success metrics:**\\n1. [METRIC 1]\\n2. [METRIC 2]"},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Everyday AI","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Write a LinkedIn Post from a Rough Idea","prompt":"Turn this rough idea into a LinkedIn post: [your rough idea or bullet points]. Make it engaging but not cringe. Open with a hook, share one insight or story, end with a question or takeaway. Keep it under 200 words.","tags":["linkedin","social-media","writing","quick"],"best_for":"Professionals who want to build a presence but hate writing from scratch","outcome":"A 200-word LinkedIn post with a hook opening and clear takeaway.","inputs":[{"label":"your rough idea or bullet points"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"We almost launched the wrong product.\\n\\nThree months ago, we were convinced users wanted a dashboard. We built mockups, wrote specs, and had the engineers ready to start.\\n\\nThen we did 8 customer calls.\\n\\nNobody cared about the dashboard. They cared about one thing: getting their data out faster. The dashboard was just how they thought they\'d use it.\\n\\nWe killed the dashboard. Built a one-click export instead. Shipped in 2 weeks. NPS jumped 18 points.\\n\\nThe lesson: users describe solutions, not problems. Your job is to ask one layer deeper — *why* do you want that?\\n\\nWhat\'s the last assumption a customer call killed for you?"},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"Write Your First Image Generation Prompt","prompt":"I want to create an image of [what you want to see]. Help me write a detailed Midjourney or DALL-E prompt that will produce a great result. Include: subject, style, lighting, mood, composition, and any negative prompts to avoid. Give me 3 variations at different style directions.","tags":["image-generation","midjourney","dalle","prompt-engineering"],"best_for":"Anyone new to AI image generation","outcome":"Three ready-to-use image prompts at different style directions, with negative prompts included.","inputs":[{"label":"what you want to see"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Stable Diffusion"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Variation 1 — Cinematic Photo**\\n`/imagine a lone lighthouse on rocky cliffs at golden hour, stormy ocean in background, dramatic god rays through clouds, shot on Hasselblad, f/2.8, cinematic color grade, 8k --ar 16:9 --v 6`\\n*Negative:* cartoonish, flat, oversaturated, text\\n\\n**Variation 2 — Oil Painting**\\n`/imagine lighthouse on sea cliffs, oil painting in the style of J.M.W. Turner, impressionistic brushwork, warm ochre and deep navy palette, museum quality, impasto texture --ar 4:3 --stylize 800`\\n*Negative:* photorealistic, digital, modern\\n\\n**Variation 3 — Minimal Illustration**\\n`/imagine minimalist vector illustration of lighthouse, flat design, 3-color palette of cream/navy/coral, geometric shapes, editorial style, negative space composition --ar 1:1 --style raw`\\n*Negative:* complex, detailed, photographic"},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"AI Product Photography Brief","prompt":"I\'m shooting [product name] using AI image generation. Create a detailed photography brief for 5 different shots: lifestyle, detail, comparison, hero, and social square. For each shot include the full AI prompt, lighting setup, background, mood, and intended platform use.","tags":["product-photography","e-commerce","midjourney","brand"],"best_for":"E-commerce brands, product marketers, studio directors","outcome":"5-shot AI photography brief with full prompts, lighting, and platform specs for each.","inputs":[{"label":"product name"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Adobe Firefly"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Shot 1 — Hero**\\nPrompt: `minimalist ceramic coffee mug, studio white background, single soft key light from upper left, long shadow, shot on Phase One, product photography, hyper-detail --ar 4:5`\\nPlatform: Homepage hero, email header\\n\\n**Shot 2 — Lifestyle**\\nPrompt: `ceramic mug on weathered oak desk, morning light through linen curtains, MacBook open, small succulent, warm lifestyle photography, film grain --ar 16:9`\\nPlatform: Instagram, blog\\n\\n**Shot 3 — Detail**\\nPrompt: `extreme close-up ceramic texture, matte glaze, micro detail, macro lens, soft bokeh background, neutral tones --ar 1:1`\\nPlatform: PDPs, Amazon\\n..."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"Midjourney Style Guide for a Brand","prompt":"Create a Midjourney style guide for [brand name] with the following brand values: [list 3 values] and target audience: [describe audience]. Include: a core prompt suffix all images should use, 5 approved style references with example prompts, 3 things to always avoid, and a color palette description to include in prompts.","tags":["brand","midjourney","style-guide","visual-identity"],"best_for":"Brand designers, marketing teams, creative directors","outcome":"A reusable Midjourney style guide with core suffix, 5 style references, and brand-safe guardrails.","inputs":[{"label":"brand name"},{"label":"list 3 values"},{"label":"describe audience"}],"tools":["Midjourney","Notion"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Brand:** Forma Studio (minimal architecture firm)\\n\\n**Core suffix** (append to every prompt):\\n`--style raw --ar 16:9 --v 6.1 :: warm ivory and slate tones, natural light, architectural precision, editorial calm`\\n\\n**Approved styles:**\\n1. Exterior — `concrete and glass building, golden hour, aerial perspective, Zaha Hadid influence`\\n2. Interior — `open plan living space, floor-to-ceiling windows, linen furniture, minimal decor`\\n...\\n\\n**Always avoid:** busy patterns, bright saturated colors, people in foreground, text overlays, fantasy elements\\n\\n**Color palette to include:** ivory (#F7F4EE), slate (#4A5568), warm sand (#C9B99A)"},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Video & Motion","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"AI Video Script and Shot List","prompt":"Write a 60-second video script and shot list for [video concept] targeting [target audience]. Format it as a production doc with: VO script column, visual description column, shot type, and AI video prompt for each scene (suitable for Runway, Pika, or Sora). Aim for 6-8 scenes.","tags":["video","runway","sora","scriptwriting","production"],"best_for":"Content creators, video producers, social media managers","outcome":"A 60-second production doc with VO script, shot descriptions, and AI video prompts for each scene.","inputs":[{"label":"video concept"},{"label":"target audience"}],"tools":["Runway","Pika","Sora","CapCut"],"output_kind":"deck","sample_output":"**VIDEO: \\"Morning Ritual\\" — Cold Brew Brand | 60 sec**\\n\\n| Scene | VO Script | Visual | Shot | AI Prompt |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| 1 (0–5s) | \\"Some mornings ask more of you.\\" | Alarm clock 5:47am, dark room | Close-up | `alarm clock glowing in dark bedroom, cinematic, slow motion, film grain, cool tones` |\\n| 2 (5–12s) | \\"So we made a cold brew that answers back.\\" | Hands wrapping around glass | Medium | `hands holding glass of cold brew coffee, morning light, condensation on glass, warm tones` |\\n..."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Character Design Sheet with AI","prompt":"I\'m designing a character: [character description]. Create a complete AI art direction document for generating a consistent character across multiple images. Include: a canonical base prompt, 4 pose variants, 3 expression variants, lighting setup for hero vs. action shots, and a LoRA/style consistency note for Stable Diffusion.","tags":["character-design","stable-diffusion","concept-art","game-art"],"best_for":"Game designers, illustrators, concept artists, indie developers","outcome":"A full character art direction sheet with canonical prompt, pose/expression variants, and SD consistency notes.","inputs":[{"label":"character description"}],"tools":["Stable Diffusion","Midjourney","ComfyUI"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Character:** Lyra — young mage, silver hair, emerald eyes, worn leather coat, staff\\n\\n**Canonical base prompt:**\\n`lyra, 20s female mage, silver hair swept back, emerald eyes glowing faintly, worn brown leather duster, wooden staff with orb, fantasy, detailed illustration, artstation quality`\\n\\n**Pose variants:**\\n- Standing neutral: `standing pose, three-quarter view, neutral expression`\\n- Casting spell: `dynamic casting pose, hands raised, magical energy swirling`\\n\\n**SD consistency tip:** Train a LoRA on 15-20 approved outputs. Use `lyra_v1:0.8` in prompt weight to maintain face/costume consistency across scenes."},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Design Tools","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Generate a Full UI Design System Prompt Library","prompt":"I\'m building a [product type] app with these design principles: [list 3 principles]. Create a prompt library for generating UI assets with AI image tools: icon set style prompt, illustration style prompt, hero image prompt, onboarding screen mood board prompt, and empty state illustration prompt. Each should be immediately usable in Midjourney or DALL-E.","tags":["ui-design","design-system","midjourney","product-design"],"best_for":"Product designers, UI/UX designers, design system leads","outcome":"5 reusable AI prompts covering icons, illustrations, heroes, onboarding, and empty states — all in a consistent visual language.","inputs":[{"label":"product type"},{"label":"list 3 principles"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Figma"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**App:** Wellness tracker | Principles: calm, human, minimal\\n\\n**Icon set:** `line icon set, wellness and health theme, 24px grid, 1.5px stroke, rounded caps, monochrome, clean minimal style, SVG-ready, white on dark --ar 1:1`\\n\\n**Illustration:** `gentle pastel illustration, person meditating in nature, flat design, soft gradients, breathing space, Headspace-adjacent style, no text --ar 4:3`\\n\\n**Hero image:** `serene landscape at dawn, soft golden light, person on hill, minimalist, editorial photography feel, lots of sky --ar 16:9`\\n\\n**Empty state:** `friendly abstract shape, no data yet, pastel tones, encouraging feeling, tiny character looking up, white background --ar 3:2`"},{"domain":"Creative AI","section":"Image Generation","skill_level":"BEGINNER","title":"AI Interior Design Concepts","prompt":"I want to redesign my [room type] in the style of [design style]. Generate 3 interior design concept prompts I can use in Midjourney or DALL-E. Include furniture, lighting, palette, and the specific mood for each concept. Make each concept distinctly different.","tags":["interior-design","home","midjourney","visualization"],"best_for":"Homeowners, renters, interior design enthusiasts","outcome":"Three distinct interior design concept prompts ready for AI image generation.","inputs":[{"label":"room type"},{"label":"design style"}],"tools":["Midjourney","DALL-E 3","Interior AI"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Concept 1 — Warm Japandi**\\n`living room interior, japandi style, warm oak furniture, cream boucle sofa, washi paper pendant light, low coffee table with single book and plant, tatami-inspired textures, golden hour light --ar 16:9`\\n\\n**Concept 2 — Cool Minimalist**\\n`living room, brutalist minimalism, concrete floor, slate grey sectional, single arc floor lamp, large art print, negative space, cool natural light --ar 16:9`\\n\\n**Concept 3 — Cosy Eclectic**\\n`boho living room, warm amber light, mixed textiles, vintage Persian rug, gallery wall, trailing houseplants, low warm lighting, layered --ar 16:9`"},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Game Design","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"Design a Core Game Loop","prompt":"I\'m building a [game genre] game for [target platform]. Help me design the core game loop. Define: the player\'s primary action, the immediate feedback, the short-term goal (session), the long-term goal (progression), and the re-engagement hook. Then identify the 3 biggest risks that could make the loop feel unsatisfying.","tags":["game-design","game-loop","mechanics","prototyping"],"best_for":"Indie developers, game designers, students learning game design","outcome":"A structured core loop design with action/feedback/goals mapped out and 3 risk areas identified.","inputs":[{"label":"game genre"},{"label":"target platform"}],"tools":["Claude","Notion","Unity","Godot"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Game:** Tower Defense Roguelite (Mobile)\\n\\n**Core loop:**\\n- **Primary action:** Place and upgrade towers using earned currency\\n- **Immediate feedback:** Visual + haptic pop when a tower kills an enemy; currency counter ticks up\\n- **Session goal (5–10 min):** Survive N waves and reach the boss\\n- **Progression goal:** Unlock permanent upgrades, new tower types, harder maps\\n- **Re-engagement hook:** Daily challenge with unique constraint; streak reward system\\n\\n**Top 3 risks:**\\n1. **Upgrade overwhelm** — Too many options at once kills mobile pacing. Solution: gate by wave milestone.\\n2. **No comeback mechanic** — If a run goes bad early, players quit. Add a \'Last Stand\' emergency ability.\\n3. **Progression plateau** — If permanent upgrades cap out, endgame feels flat. Plan a prestige system from day one."},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Narrative & Dialogue","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"Write Branching NPC Dialogue","prompt":"Write branching dialogue for an NPC named [NPC name] who is [personality description] in a [game setting]. The player needs to [player goal in this interaction]. Create 3 conversation paths: friendly approach, aggressive approach, and clever/persuasion approach. Each path should have 3 exchanges and end with a different outcome.","tags":["narrative","dialogue","npc","rpg","game-writing"],"best_for":"Game writers, narrative designers, RPG developers","outcome":"Three fully-written branching dialogue paths with distinct outcomes for different player approaches.","inputs":[{"label":"NPC name"},{"label":"personality description"},{"label":"game setting"},{"label":"player goal in this interaction"}],"tools":["Claude","Twine","Ink","Unity"],"output_kind":"templates","sample_output":"**NPC:** Maren — tired city guard, underpaid, secretly sympathetic\\n\\n**PATH A — Friendly**\\nPlayer: \\"Rough shift?\\"\\nMaren: \\"You have no idea. Third double this week. What do you need?\\"\\nPlayer: \\"Just trying to get into the merchants\' quarter.\\"\\nMaren: *sighs* \\"Gate closes at ninth bell. But… I didn\'t see you walk through just now. Move quick.\\"\\n*Outcome: Passage granted, +5 reputation with City Guard faction*\\n\\n**PATH B — Aggressive**\\nPlayer: \\"Get out of my way.\\"\\nMaren: \\"Excuse me? You want to try that again?\\"\\n*Outcome: Hostile, -10 City Guard reputation, forced combat or retreat*\\n\\n**PATH C — Persuasion**\\nPlayer: \\"I heard the captain skims the gate fees. Must be frustrating doing the work and seeing none of it.\\"\\nMaren: *quietly* \\"Who told you that?\\" *pause* \\"Fine. But you didn\'t hear this from me.\\"\\n*Outcome: Access + quest hook: Expose corrupt captain*"},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Programming","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Generate Unity C# Game Systems","prompt":"I\'m building a [game type] in Unity. Write a clean, commented C# script for [specific system]. The system should: [list 3 requirements]. Use Unity best practices: SerializeField for inspector exposure, coroutines where appropriate, and the observer pattern via events for decoupling. Include a brief architecture note at the top.","tags":["unity","csharp","game-programming","systems"],"best_for":"Unity developers, indie game programmers, CS students","outcome":"A production-quality Unity C# script with architecture notes, events-based design, and full comments.","inputs":[{"label":"game type"},{"label":"specific system"},{"label":"list 3 requirements"}],"tools":["Unity","Visual Studio","Claude"],"output_kind":"code","sample_output":"```csharp\\n// InventorySystem.cs\\n// Architecture: Uses event-driven design to decouple UI from inventory logic.\\n// Subscribe to OnInventoryChanged to update any UI without direct references.\\n\\nusing UnityEngine;\\nusing System;\\nusing System.Collections.Generic;\\n\\npublic class InventorySystem : MonoBehaviour\\n{\\n    public static event Action<List<Item>> OnInventoryChanged;\\n\\n    [SerializeField] private int maxSlots = 20;\\n    private List<Item> _items = new List<Item>();\\n\\n    public bool AddItem(Item item)\\n    {\\n        if (_items.Count >= maxSlots) return false;\\n        _items.Add(item);\\n        OnInventoryChanged?.Invoke(_items);\\n        return true;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void RemoveItem(Item item)\\n    {\\n        if (_items.Remove(item))\\n            OnInventoryChanged?.Invoke(_items);\\n    }\\n}\\n```"},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Game Design","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Balance a Game Economy","prompt":"I have a [game genre] with this economy: [describe currency, sources, and sinks]. Players are reporting that [specific problem: inflation / deflation / pay-to-win feeling / etc]. Diagnose the root cause, propose 3 fixes with trade-offs, and give me a spreadsheet schema I can use to model the economy before implementing changes.","tags":["game-economy","balancing","monetization","design"],"best_for":"Game designers, live ops teams, monetization designers","outcome":"Root-cause diagnosis, 3 fixes with trade-offs, and a spreadsheet schema for economy modeling.","inputs":[{"label":"game genre"},{"label":"describe currency, sources, and sinks"},{"label":"specific problem: inflation / deflation / pay-to-win feeling / etc"}],"tools":["Claude","Google Sheets","Excel"],"output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Diagnosis:** Soft currency inflation\\n\\nYour daily quest rewards (500 coins) outpace the primary sink (upgrades average 800 coins but only needed every 3 days). Players accumulate ~1,500 coins/day with nowhere to spend them, making purchases feel meaningless.\\n\\n**Fix 1 — Add a time-limited sink**\\nFlash merchant appears daily with exclusive cosmetics for 2,000 coins. *Trade-off:* Requires art/content overhead.\\n\\n**Fix 2 — Reduce quest rewards by 30%**\\nSimple lever, ships fast. *Trade-off:* Risk of player backlash; needs communication.\\n\\n**Fix 3 — Add a prestige/conversion system**\\n10,000 coins → 1 premium token. Creates an aspirational sink. *Trade-off:* Competitive pressure with IAP.\\n\\n**Spreadsheet schema:**\\n| Day | Coins earned | Coins spent | Net | Running total | Active sinks |"},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"AI & Agents","skill_level":"EXPERT","title":"Design an LLM-Powered NPC Brain","prompt":"I want to build an NPC in [game engine] that uses an LLM for dynamic dialogue and decision-making. Design the complete architecture: context window management strategy, memory system (short + long term), personality consistency mechanism, cost-control approach, and fallback for offline/slow responses. Include a sample system prompt and the API call structure.","tags":["llm","ai-npc","game-ai","agents","architecture"],"best_for":"Advanced game developers, AI engineers building game AI","outcome":"Full LLM-NPC architecture with memory design, cost controls, system prompt, and API structure.","inputs":[{"label":"game engine"}],"tools":["Claude API","OpenAI API","Unity","Unreal Engine"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Architecture: LLM NPC Brain v1**\\n\\n**Context window strategy:**\\n- Fixed system prompt: ~800 tokens (personality, world, current state)\\n- Rolling dialogue window: last 10 exchanges (~600 tokens)\\n- Injected memory summary: top 3 relevant memories (~200 tokens)\\n- Total budget: 1,600 tokens in, 200 tokens out\\n\\n**Memory system:**\\n- Short-term: last 10 messages in RAM\\n- Long-term: vector DB (Chroma) — embed each exchange, retrieve top-3 by cosine similarity at query time\\n\\n**System prompt skeleton:**\\n```\\nYou are Aldric, a suspicious tavern keeper in the city of Veth.\\nPersonality: guarded, dry humour, loyal to paying customers.\\nCurrent state: {npc_mood}, {time_of_day}, {player_reputation}\\nRecent memory: {memory_summary}\\nRespond in 1-2 sentences. Stay in character. Never break the fourth wall.\\n```\\n\\n**Cost control:** Cache system prompt with Anthropic prompt caching. Use Haiku for ambient chatter, Sonnet for quest-critical dialogue."},{"domain":"Game Development","section":"Procedural Generation","skill_level":"EXPERT","title":"Procedural Level Design System","prompt":"Design a procedural level generation system for a [game genre]. Define: the grammar rules (what elements can follow what), the constraint system (difficulty curve, pacing, accessibility), the seeded random approach, and the validation step that ensures every generated level is beatable. Give me pseudocode for the generator and a sample level output.","tags":["procedural-generation","level-design","algorithms","game-programming"],"best_for":"Advanced game developers, technical designers","outcome":"A complete procedural level design specification with grammar rules, constraints, pseudocode, and sample output.","inputs":[{"label":"game genre"}],"tools":["Claude","Python","Unity","Godot"],"output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**System: Dungeon Crawler Level Generator**\\n\\n**Grammar rules:**\\nRoom types: [ENTRANCE, COMBAT, TREASURE, PUZZLE, BOSS]\\nSequence: ENTRANCE → (COMBAT|PUZZLE)+ → TREASURE? → BOSS\\nConstraint: No two COMBAT rooms adjacent; TREASURE only after COMBAT\\n\\n**Difficulty curve:**\\nEnemy HP = base × (1 + 0.15 × roomIndex)\\nRoom count = 8 + floor(level/3)\\n\\n**Pseudocode:**\\n```\\nfunction generateLevel(seed, difficulty):\\n  rng = SeededRandom(seed)\\n  rooms = [ENTRANCE]\\n  while not valid(rooms):\\n    rooms = buildChain(rng, difficulty)\\n  return connectRooms(rooms, rng)\\n\\nfunction validate(rooms):\\n  return isReachable(rooms) and hasBoss(rooms) and difficultyInBounds(rooms)\\n```\\n\\n**Sample output (seed 4821, difficulty 2):**\\nENTRANCE → COMBAT(3 goblins) → PUZZLE(pressure plates) → COMBAT(5 goblins + archer) → TREASURE(rare sword) → BOSS(Lich, 240HP)"},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"AI & Agents","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Build a Personal Finance AI Agent","prompt":"I want to build a local AI agent that connects to my bank accounts via [bank API or CSV export], stores transactions in a local SQLite database, and runs a daily summary that categorises spending, flags anomalies, and suggests actions. Design the full agent architecture: data ingestion pipeline, categorisation prompt, anomaly-detection logic, and the daily briefing prompt template. Include Python pseudocode for the main loop and the schema for the local DB.","tags":["personal-finance","ai-agent","automation","plaid","sqlite","budgeting"],"best_for":"Developers who want AI-driven personal finance automation without relying on third-party apps","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Full architecture for a self-hosted personal finance AI agent with ingestion pipeline, DB schema, categorisation logic, anomaly detection, and daily briefing template.","inputs":[{"label":"bank API or CSV export"},{"label":"spending categories"},{"label":"monthly budget targets"}],"tools":["Claude API","Plaid API","Python","SQLite"],"est_time":"3–5 hours","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Agent Architecture: Personal Finance AI**\\n\\n**DB Schema (SQLite):**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE transactions (\\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n  date TEXT, amount REAL, merchant TEXT,\\n  category TEXT, raw_category TEXT, flagged INTEGER DEFAULT 0\\n);\\nCREATE TABLE daily_summaries (date TEXT PRIMARY KEY, json TEXT);\\n```\\n\\n**Ingestion pipeline:**\\n1. Pull transactions via Plaid /transactions/sync (or parse CSV)\\n2. Upsert into SQLite (dedup by transaction id)\\n3. For each uncategorised row, call Claude with merchant name + amount → returns category\\n\\n**Categorisation prompt:**\\n```\\nClassify this transaction into one of: [Food, Transport, Housing, Subscriptions, Shopping, Health, Entertainment, Other].\\nMerchant: {merchant}  Amount: ${amount}\\nReturn only the category name.\\n```\\n\\n**Anomaly detection logic:**\\n- Flag if amount > 2× rolling 30-day average for that category\\n- Flag if merchant appears for the first time and amount > $50\\n\\n**Daily briefing prompt:**\\n```\\nGiven these transactions from {date}: {json}\\nAnd monthly budget targets: {targets}\\nWrite a 5-bullet morning briefing covering: total spend, top category, biggest single charge, any flagged anomalies, and one actionable suggestion.\\n```"},{"domain":"Finance & FP&A","section":"Financial Planning & Analysis","skill_level":"ADVANCED","title":"Tax Strategy Finder (CPA-Level Automation)","prompt":"Act as a senior CPA and tax strategist. I will give you my [income sources], [filing status], [major expenses], and [investment portfolio]. Identify the top 5 tax optimisation strategies available to me, explain the mechanism of each deduction or deferral, estimate the potential savings, flag any risks or thresholds I need to stay under, and give me a prioritised action checklist for this tax year. Reference relevant IRS code sections or equivalent for [country].","tags":["tax","tax-strategy","cpa","deductions","financial-planning","irs"],"best_for":"Self-employed professionals, investors, and business owners looking to reduce tax liability","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Ranked list of tax strategies with mechanisms, estimated savings, risk flags, and a concrete action checklist for the current tax year.","inputs":[{"label":"income sources (salary, freelance, dividends, etc.)"},{"label":"filing status (single, MFJ, etc.)"},{"label":"major expenses (home office, vehicle, health, education)"},{"label":"investment portfolio (taxable, IRA, 401k balances)"},{"label":"country"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"30 minutes","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Top 5 Tax Strategies for Your Profile**\\n\\n**1. Max Solo 401(k) — estimated savings: $14,280**\\nAs a self-employed person you can contribute up to $66,000 (2024). The employer contribution side (25% of net self-employment income) is deductible on Schedule 1. *IRC §401(a).* Action: open a Solo 401(k) by Dec 31; fund by tax deadline.\\n\\n**2. Home Office Deduction (Simplified Method) — ~$1,500**\\n$5/sq ft × up to 300 sq ft. No depreciation recapture risk. *IRC §280A.* Action: measure dedicated workspace, document with photos.\\n\\n**3. SEP-IRA vs Solo 401(k) comparison**\\nSEP-IRA simpler to open, but Solo 401(k) allows employee deferrals — better if income < $200k.\\n\\n**4. Qualified Business Income (QBI) Deduction — up to 20% of net income**\\nAvailable for pass-through entities below $182,050 (single). *IRC §199A.* Risk: phase-out applies to specified service trades.\\n\\n**5. Tax-Loss Harvesting on taxable portfolio**\\nRealise ~$8k in unrealised losses to offset gains. Beware 30-day wash-sale rule. *IRC §1091.*\\n\\n**Action checklist:**\\n- [ ] Open Solo 401(k) before Dec 31\\n- [ ] Calculate exact home office sq footage\\n- [ ] Review taxable account for harvesting candidates\\n- [ ] Confirm QBI eligibility with your business type"},{"domain":"Quick Wins","section":"Personal Productivity","skill_level":"INTERMEDIATE","title":"AI Health Data Tracker & Interpreter","prompt":"I will paste the results from my recent [blood work / health metrics]. Interpret each value, flag anything outside the optimal range (not just the lab reference range), explain what each flagged value might indicate, suggest 3 lifestyle or dietary adjustments I could discuss with my doctor, and format the output as a clear summary table followed by the action points. Do not diagnose — focus on pattern recognition and evidence-based context.","tags":["health","blood-work","biometrics","wellness","personal-data","tracking"],"best_for":"Health-conscious individuals who want to understand their lab results and prepare smarter doctor conversations","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Clear interpretation of health metrics with optimal vs. reference range comparison, pattern flags, lifestyle suggestions, and a ready-to-use doctor conversation summary.","inputs":[{"label":"blood work or health metrics (paste raw values)"},{"label":"age and biological sex"},{"label":"known conditions or medications (optional)"}],"tools":["Claude","ChatGPT"],"est_time":"10 minutes","output_kind":"analysis","sample_output":"**Health Metrics Summary**\\n\\n| Marker | Your Value | Lab Range | Optimal Range | Status |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| LDL Cholesterol | 142 mg/dL | <160 | <100 | ⚠️ Elevated |\\n| HbA1c | 5.8% | <5.7 pre-diabetic | <5.4 | ⚠️ Borderline |\\n| Vitamin D | 24 ng/mL | 20–50 | 40–60 | ⚠️ Sub-optimal |\\n| Ferritin | 68 ng/mL | 12–300 | 50–150 | ✅ Good |\\n| TSH | 2.1 mIU/L | 0.4–4.0 | 0.5–2.5 | ✅ Good |\\n\\n**Flagged patterns:**\\n- LDL + borderline HbA1c together suggest early metabolic stress worth monitoring.\\n- Low-normal Vitamin D may be contributing to fatigue.\\n\\n**Lifestyle adjustments to discuss with your doctor:**\\n1. Mediterranean-style diet to address LDL and glycaemic trends simultaneously.\\n2. Vitamin D3 + K2 supplementation (2,000–4,000 IU/day) — confirm dose with doctor.\\n3. 150 min/week moderate cardio — independently improves all three flagged markers.\\n\\n*This is pattern recognition, not medical advice. Bring this table to your next appointment.*"},{"domain":"Software Development","section":"AI & Agents","skill_level":"EXPERT","title":"Ghost Database for AI Agents","prompt":"Design a persistent memory and knowledge layer — a \'ghost database\' — for a long-running AI agent system built with [framework/stack]. The system must support: short-term episodic memory (recent conversation turns), long-term semantic memory (vector search over past interactions and documents), structured fact storage (key-value entities the agent can update), and a retrieval strategy that selects the right memory type at inference time. Provide the full schema, the retrieval orchestration logic, a sample system-prompt injection template, and guidance on when to write vs. read from each store.","tags":["ai-agent","memory","vector-db","architecture","rag","persistent-state","llm-ops"],"best_for":"AI engineers building autonomous agents that need reliable long-term memory and context management","source":"Wes Roth — \\"AI just BROKE the ENTIRE INDUSTRY...\\"","outcome":"Complete ghost-database architecture spec with schemas for all three memory types, retrieval orchestration pseudocode, system-prompt injection template, and write/read decision rules.","inputs":[{"label":"framework/stack (LangChain, custom Python, etc.)"},{"label":"agent\'s primary domain or task"},{"label":"expected conversation volume (light / heavy)"}],"tools":["Claude API","OpenAI API","Chroma","Pinecone","Redis","PostgreSQL","Python"],"est_time":"2–4 hours","output_kind":"spec","sample_output":"**Ghost Database Architecture**\\n\\n**Memory layers:**\\n\\n| Layer | Store | TTL | Use case |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Episodic (short-term) | Redis list (sliding window) | Last 20 turns | Recent dialogue context |\\n| Semantic (long-term) | ChromaDB / Pinecone | Permanent | Past interactions, docs |\\n| Structured facts | PostgreSQL key-value table | Permanent, mutable | User prefs, entity state |\\n\\n**Structured facts schema:**\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE agent_facts (\\n  agent_id TEXT, key TEXT, value JSONB,\\n  confidence REAL, updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\\n  PRIMARY KEY (agent_id, key)\\n);\\n```\\n\\n**Retrieval orchestration (pseudocode):**\\n```python\\ndef build_context(query, agent_id):\\n  episodic  = redis.lrange(f\'ep:{agent_id}\', 0, 19)      # always include\\n  semantic  = chroma.query(query, n_results=4)             # top-4 semantic hits\\n  facts     = pg.fetch(\'SELECT key, value FROM agent_facts WHERE agent_id=$1\', agent_id)\\n  return format_context(episodic, semantic, facts)\\n```\\n\\n**System-prompt injection template:**\\n```\\n[MEMORY]\\nRecent context: {episodic_summary}\\nRelevant past knowledge: {semantic_hits}\\nKnown facts about user: {facts_json}\\n[/MEMORY]\\n```\\n\\n**Write rules:**\\n- After every turn → append to episodic Redis list, pop oldest if > 20\\n- After task completion → embed summary → upsert to vector DB\\n- When agent learns a stable fact (name, preference, goal) → upsert to PostgreSQL facts table"}]');

